title: crab ball
directions: Form into ball and chill.
When ready to serve, pour cocktail sauce over top.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Arrange chicken, bones up, in a 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Peel and slice potatoes; place around chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste and add some garlic salt.
Add the water.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, until chicken is brown, then turn chicken and potatoes over and bake for about 45 minutes more until tender.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ham slice with sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes; slice.
Place in greased baking dish in layers; sprinkling each layer with brown sugar and dotting with butter.
Brown ham slice in skillet over low heat; place ham in skillet over low heat; place ham slice over sweet potatoes.
Rinse frying pan with 1/4 c. water; pour over casserole.
Bake at 250 to 300 degrees until ham and potatoes are tender, about 1 hour.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp 2 minutes in water with shrimp boil.
Peel and marinate with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: fat free dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill overnight (at least 4 hours).

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Blend cream cheese and dressing mix together.
Form into a ball.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
A few minutes before serving, roll hardened ball in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: First Layer:
Blend together butter, flour and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Press in with hand.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Whip with fork until liquid is absorbed and becomes a thick mixture.
Combine salt, flour and Crisco mixture.
Stir into a dough. Work until smooth on floured surface.
Yields one double 9-inch pie crust.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar and add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and stir in zucchini, raisins, pineapple, walnuts, coconut and vanilla. Bake in 3 small or 2 large greased pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy almond candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt candy coating with condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in almond extract, then almonds.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined, 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into triangles or squares. Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: 10 minute dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixer bowl and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Make sauce.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add Parmesan cheese and cavatelli.
Make cheese layer.
In bowl combine remaining ingredients in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 cavatelli mixture.
Layer with cheese mixture.
Spoon remaining cavatelli.
Arrange Mozzarella cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
(Parmesan cheese can be substituted for sugar.)
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix lemon juice, sweetened condensed milk, cherry pie filling and whipped topping.
Mix in almond extract.
Mix in other ingredients and chill.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt in a large bowl; add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.
Spread marshmallows to cover cake.
Put into oven and remove when marshmallows are melted.

title: mocha cooler
directions: Pour coffee into blender; spoon in ice cream, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Blend 10 to 15 seconds (or beat all ingredients with rotary beater).
Serve immediately over ice cubes in tall glasses.
Yields 3 or 4 servings.

title: cabbage joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add ketchup and next 4 ingredients; heat.
Combine quickly with cabbage.
Spoon approximately 1/2 cup on each bun.
Serve while filling is hot.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: noodles
directions: Mix together; roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Roll mixture up into roll.
Cut into strips.
Separate and drop into boiling broth.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Cook 5 cups shredded cabbage in 1/2-inch of salted water (1/2 teaspoon to 1 cup of water) with 2 tablespoons vinegar added.
Heat water to boiling.
Cover.
Cook cabbage, 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain. Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Drain fat from skillet, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Stir brown sugar and flour into fat in skillet.
Stir in water, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Stir bacon and sauce mixture into hot cabbage in saucepan; heat through.

title: holston's favorite chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 3-quarts water.
When cooked, remove chicken and debone, putting meat aside.
Bring stock to a boil and add dumplings, one at a time, stirring often to prevent sticking. After dumplings are all in, reduce heat, cover and cook 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Return chicken to dumplings.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick comes out of center clean.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add chocolate chips.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Stir into flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Serves 25 or 30.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk with instant pudding. Add oranges and pineapple and mix by hand.	Cut cookies into little pieces. Add cookies and whipped topping. Refrigerate.

title: butter pecan candy
directions: Combine pecans and margarine and toast in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and cool.
Melt cream cheese over low heat.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar gradually.
Add the 1 teaspoon vanilla and cooled pecans.
Pour into a buttered dish and chill before cutting into squares.

title: bean dip
directions: Use low bowl and place ingredients in layers, starting with first ingredient at the bottom.
Use layers of approximately 1/2-inch.
The amount required depends on the size of the bowl.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Remove from frypan.
In pan add water and bouillon cubes and stir until cubes are dissolved. Add rice, diced onion, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Put chops on rice.
Top each with a slice of onion, tomato and green pepper (if pepper is desired).
Cover and cook at 300° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: simple bacon and cheese quiche
directions: Place all ingredients, except bacon and grated cheese, in a blender.
Blend for about 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into a well buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon and grated cheese on top of mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes. You may need to loosely cover the quiche with a piece of foil during the last 15 minutes to prevent top from burning.
Let cool slightly.
Cut and serve.

title: quickie taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and green pepper in skillet; drain.
Add seasoning, corn and sauce in ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine potatoes, cheese sauce mix, meat mixture and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake covered for 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: spritz christmas cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond extract; beat well.
Sift
flour and baking powder, add gradually to creamed mixture, mixing to a smooth dough.
Do not chill.
Force dough through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 400 degrees for 8 minutes and cool. Makes 6 dozen.

title: succulent rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Place roast in a roasting pan. Roast for 15 minutes, reduce oven to 400 degrees.
Continue roasting for about 20 minutes per pound for medium.
Remove roast from oven, place on serving platter, keep warm.
Blend flour into pan juices, cook over medium heat, scraping pan to loosen brown bits, for about 4-5 minutes.
Gradually stir in water or beef broth.
Cook over medium-high heat stirring continually, until mixture boils.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Slice roast and serve with pan gravy.
Serves four.

title: raspberries in orange juice cocktail
directions: Arrange 1/3 of the raspberries in sherbet glasses.
Combine the orange juice and lime juice and sweeten, if desired.
Stir well and pour over the raspberries, allowing about 1/3 cup for each glass.
Chill until ready to serve, then garnish each with a sprig of mint.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash. Cook in boiling water until done. Drain.
Add butter and mash.
Add all other ingredients. Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first four ingredients until fluffy.
Add all ingredients.
Divide between two greased loaf pans,
fill pans half-full.
Bake for one hour.

title: cajun beans
directions: Wash and boil dry beans in 2 quarts of water with 2 tablespoons of soda for 15 minutes.
Pour off water and wash beans thoroughly.
Put beans back in pan with 2 1/2 quarts of boiling water.
Add garlic, bay leaves, rosemary, Cajun seasoning and brown sugar.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk in top of double boiler. Combine dry cake mix, remaining milk, butter and nuts; stirring until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over crust.
Pour caramel mixture over morsels, spreading evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramels. Return to oven; bake 15 to 20 more minutes.
Cool; chill 30 minutes.
Cut into small bars.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Mix sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube/Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana surprise bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add banana and egg, mixing well.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir creamed mixture into the flour mixture (add nuts, cherries or fruit, if you like). Pour half of batter into the pan.
Lay the banana in the batter; cover with remaining batter.
Bake about 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: fresh herb vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered jar; shake to mix.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve with raw vegetables. Serves 6 to 10.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add broccoli and cornbread mix. Bake in greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Cut cheese into blocks, melt in crockpot. Add tomatoes, hamburger and taco mix, mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter or spray with Pam a casserole dish.
Sprinkle dressing mix to cover bottom of dish.
Mix ingredients and pour in dish. Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until firm.

title: fort cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Press with back of fork in a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes. Makes 18 to 24 cookies.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 1 cup flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Spread in greased 11 x 14 inch pan.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and remaining ingredients; spread over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: taco soup(weight watchers)
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain. Mix Hidden Valley
Ranch mix with taco seasoning into meat. Then without draining, add all of the other ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour. Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: dellarosa rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice in milk 1 1/2 hour until very tender.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks lightly and add to cooked rice.
Add 1 1/3 cup sugar and salt, lemon rind, 1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract and butter.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set casserole in pan of water (hot) and bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: dump muffins
directions: In a large bowl, dump cranberries.
Add eggs, Mazola, honey and sugar; mix well.
Add All Bran, flour, baking powder, baking soda and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pear muffins
directions: Cream together beaten eggs, oil and sugars. Add flour, soda and cinnamon. Add vanilla. Mix well. Add pears (coconut and pecans). Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 4.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook the celery in small amount of boiling water 8 minutes; drain well.
Saute onion in small amount of butter until tender. Combine soup, water chestnuts and pimientos; mix well.
Stir in celery and onion.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish. Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over celery mixture, then top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into 9-inch pie pan, making continuous crusts. Brown turkey and sprinkle with beef bouillon.
Add onions and peppers, salt and black pepper.
After meat is cooked, add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Put 1/2 meat mixture in unbaked crust.
Spread 1/2 cheese on top.
Cover with remaining meat mixture and rest of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package directions. Immediately sprinkle marshmallows over brownies; continue baking until marshmallows begin to melt.
Melt chocolate with milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over marshmallows; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: custard vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix all ingredients until creamy smooth.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife cut comes out clean.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Form meat into 4 patties.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onion; place over meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Wrap each serving in aluminum foil.
Place in baking dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly. Chill overnight.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, meat and onion powder.
Put into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix biscuit mix and 1 1/2 cups milk and pour evenly over soup mixture. Sprinkle with fresh parsley.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes, or until sauce starts to thicken. Brush on country ribs or chicken.
Excellent on the grill.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Brown hamburger. Layer beans, beef, chilies and sauce. Microwave at 70%
power for 8 minutes. Top with cheese and melt 2 minutes.

title: fried trout
directions: Wash fish under cold running water.
Pat dry. Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper. Roll each fish in mixture. Dip them in beaten egg and then roll them again in mixture.
Place them on foil and refrigerate 30 minutes before frying.
Fill a deep heavy pot within 3-inches of rim with oil.
Heat to 375°.
Gently lower two of the fish into the hot fat and fry until lightly brown (about 3 to 3 1/2 minutes).
Remove with slotted spatula.
Place on paper towel to drain and repeat with remaining fish. Keep fish warm in a 200° oven.
Serves 3.

title: eggs with creole sauce
directions: Brown onion and pepper in
margarine. Add flour and tomatoes. Cook 10 minutes. Take a slice of bread and cut a hole in the middle.
Place bread in skillet with plenty of margarine and drop an egg into the center. Fry on both sides until nicely brown. Serve sauce over the bread.

title: sherbet and jello
directions: Put jello in bowl.
Add boiling water and dissolve.
Cool slightly.
Drain pineapple and orange slices.
Add pineapple, orange slices, sherbet, whipped cream and marshmallows; blend well.
Do not stir too much.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Refrigerate to set.
Serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar, milk and flavoring together.
Mix in flour, roll out on floured board and cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake at 400° until they begin to brown.

title: pineapple cobbler
directions: Combine ingredients; pour over pie crust in medium size pan Top with top crust; cut into strips.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Pick chicken off of bones.
Mix flour and Crisco.
Add 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth until very stiff.
Roll out; pinch off into chicken and hot broth.
Let cook until the dumplings are done.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla together.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin together and keep melted over hot water.
Place small amount of chocolate in each cup of miniature muffin papers or tins.
Shape rounded teaspoon of creamed mixture and place on soft chocolate in pan. Drizzle chocolate over confectioners-peanut butter patties to cover.
Chill and remove from pan.
To remove from tins, warm bottoms of muffin cups with towel wet in hot water.
Continue until all mixture is shaped.
To haste shaping, roll up small balls of creamed mixture and dip in melted chocolate to make bonbons.

To make the pie, you would probably pour the creamed mixture into the graham cracker shell and then spread top with the milk chocolate bits and run under broiler until melted. Spread to edges with knife and chill.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add fruit.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in.
Dampen crust edges to seal.
Very tart fruit may require up to 1/2 cup sugar for 1 quart of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Add all ingredients to blender. Add ice cubes one at a time.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Cream together peanut butter and shortening and blend well.
Add sugar, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla and blend well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Using 1 teaspoon of dough, roll into a ball, roll in granulated sugar and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes, remove and press a candy kiss in center of each cookie. Return to oven for 2 minutes (no more).
Remove and place on tray to cool.
Repeat with rest of dough.
Makes about 4 dozen and kids love them.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses until light and fluffy.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir into molasses mixture until well blended.
Roll into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line shallow cooking pan with aluminum foil.
Cut wings at each joint, discarding tips.
Melt butter flavored Crisco in lined pan.
Combine flour, onion salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces one at a time; shake to coat.
Place in pan; bake 25 minutes.
Turn; bake another 25 minutes or until crisp.
Transfer to paper towels.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: four-minute basic gravy
directions: Blend oil and flour in a nonstick pan.
Using a rubber spatula, slowly stir in cold milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add onion powder.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it thickens. Cooking time is about 3 minutes.
Add ready-made brown gravy concentrate and pepper for meat sauce.
Add capers, dill, pepper and a dash of lemon for fish.
Add sliced canned mushrooms and garlic powder for mushroom sauce.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Microwave Power: High.
Total Time: 7 to 10 minutes.

title: cincinnati five way chili
directions: Salt a large skillet.
Turn the heat to medium.
Add the meat, onion and garlic.
Break up meat with fork and cook until browned. Drain fat.
Add barbecue sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Add spices.
Cover and simmer at very low heat 30 minutes, stirring and tasting occasionally, adding tomato juice if the mixture becomes too dry.
This chili is best after being allowed to age overnight in the refrigerator.
To construct a plate of five way, layer spaghetti on a plate.
Top with hot chili and a sparse layer of beans, then onions.
Top with plenty of cheese while chili is still hot.
Serve with oyster crackers on the side.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crust from all sides of bread; discard crust.
Cut bread into one-inch cubes and set aside.
Combine cheeses and margarine in top of double boiler; cook until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Fold a small amount of hot cheese mixture into egg whites, then fold into remaining cheese mixture.
Use fork to dip each bread cube into cheese mixture, coating bread on all sides.
Place cubes one-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, or freeze.
Remove from refrigerator or freezer and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store mix in airtight container until ready to use.
For 1 serving, place 1 well-rounded teaspoon in cup and fill with boiling water.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening, then yeast and milk. Mix with large spoon real good.
Keep in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix corn syrup, sugar and cream of tartar; bring to hard boil stage.
Add rest of ingredients.
If you use marshmallows, they need to be melted first.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; stir well.
Add to melted butter and then add peaches and peach juice. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream the sugar, butter and shortening.
Add one egg at a time, beating well.
Combine milk and flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder; add alternately to sugar mixture with milk and coconut.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; tear apart and mix with can of Veg-All.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with can of milk.
Pour over top of Veg-All and chicken.
Mix melted stick of butter, Bisquick and 1 cup milk for crust and slowly pour over. Cook at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Firmly shape into 6 patties.
Over medium heat, heat 10-inch skillet until very hot.
Add patties; cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until browned.
Pour off fat (with lean beef there is no fat).
Stir remaining soup and water into skillet.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally, if necessary.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Can prepare and mix meat, onion, tomato and kidney beans the day before.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients together until sugar is dissolved. (Boil a few minutes.)
Cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: rocky road chocolate candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and marshmallows, stirring constantly.
Stir for about 6 minutes.
Remove and add chips and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Add frozen marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: no bake cornflake squares
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Pour mixture over cornflakes and coconut in a large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly and pour in a lightly greased square pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: biscuit topped tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour; cook over low heat until bubbly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt, pepper and tuna.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.

title: tomato salad with cucumber dressing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour over cucumber and green peppers; let marinate 5 minutes.
Slice tomatoes and serve with cucumber mixture poured over them.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sherried chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into 3-inch pieces.
In large skillet or wok, cook chicken in oil until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer another 5 to 10 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Serves 6.

title: date bars
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Add alternately with milk into sugar mixture.
Stir in chopped dates and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool, then dust with confectioners sugar or cut in finger lengths and roll in sugar.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit.
Grease 2 quart casserole generously.
Alternate layers of fruit with sugar and tapioca.
Dot top with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Serve warm.
Good with ham or turkey.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine the first three ingredients.
Spread the cream cheese mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with the chili.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese to cover.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and spread in pan until set.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Put in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Chop cookies finely.
Mix with melted butter in a bowl.

Press into glass 9 x 11-inch baking dish, reserving 1/2 cup for topping. Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 cups whipped topping in mixer bowl until smooth. Spread mixture over cookie crust. Prepare pudding mix using package directions.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Top with remaining whipped topping. Sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes, cut in half.
Cut each half into 4 wedges. Microwave butter in 8 x 12-inch pan 45 seconds.
Mix in cheese and seasonings.
Coat wedges and place wedge side up in dish; cover and microwave 12 to 14 minutes or until tender.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Let cool slightly.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, rice, egg, salt and pepper and 1/4 cup of the tomato juice.
Cut the tops off peppers (4 or 5) and clean out.
Stuff peppers tightly and put in a saucepan.
Remove center core of the tops and put back on peppers.
Pour tomato juice in pan to not quite cover peppers.
Simmer, covered, for an hour. Remove peppers with slotted spoon.
Skim fat from juice and thicken juice with flour to make gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together; add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers and bananas in casserole dish.
Pour mixture on top and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Put in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over jello.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes. These are good to add 1/2 cup coconut.

title: punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch and 7-Up together.
Right before serving, add sherbet and orange juice.
Makes 1 large punch bowl.

title: rolls
directions: Mix 1 pint milk, sugar and Crisco.
Heat until sugar and Crisco have melted.
Add rest of milk.
Let this cool until lukewarm.
Mix 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and soda and add to liquid mixture.
Dissolve yeast and add to mixture.
Add the rest of the flour.

It will be the consistency of cake batter. Refrigerate in container large enough for it to double in size. Can be stored in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days and use as needed. Remove the dough needed; form into cloverleaf rolls; let rise about 2 hours and cook at 350° for 12 minutes.
Can be frozen when cooked.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown beef; drain, leaving 2 tablespoons of fat in skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Mix onion and ground beef.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with celery, sauce and cheese.
Mix the celery and mushroom soup together and pour over cheese.
Cover the soup mixture with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese apricot salad
directions: Mix and
cook the apricot and lemon juice, sugar, flour and eggs
until
thick.
Set
aside
to
cool.	Place
apricot halves in a dish, then the sauce, then grated cheese and nuts. Repeat.

title: blackberry pork chops
directions: Broil pork chops until done.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until mixture becomes thick (approximately 20 minutes). Pour sauce over pork chops and serve.

title: fruit dip 2
directions: Blend all ingredients in a mixer until well blended.
Chill. Serve with watermelon, strawberries, apple and bananas.

title: heavenly strawberry salad
directions: In large bowl, combine Jell-O and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in all fruit and nuts.
Turn 1/2 of this mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until set.
Stir sour cream and spread over berry mixture in dish.
Spoon rest of Jell-O over sour cream layer.
Cover and chill until set.

title: cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except egg whites).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into dough.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scotch coffee cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and flour together.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Add to mixture, salt, baking powder, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add cinnamon to the cup reserved for topping.
Bake at 350° until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Two 8-inch round cake pans do quite well with this recipe.

title: chilled mint tea
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add the tea bags and mint leaves.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove the tea bags.
Add the sugar to the hot tea; stir until dissolved. Prepare the lemonade and orange juice according to package instructions; stir into the sweetened mint tea.
Refrigerate the mixture overnight.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add flour alternately with eggs (one at a time). Beat well.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy (usually about 5 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients adding shortening last. * For peanut butter icing, use only 1 c. 10x sugar and mix peanut butter to suit your taste!

title: pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to cover to make broth.
When chicken is well cooked, remove meat from bone, cut up fine and add back into broth.
Mix flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt. Cut in shortening.
Beat egg; add enough milk to make 3/4 cup. Stir into flour mixture.
With 1/2 of dough at a time, roll out like pie dough, only thinner.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop in boiling chicken broth.
Cook 15 minutes and serve.

title: peanut ice cream pie
directions: Press half of the ice cream into crust.
In small bowl, stir corn syrup and peanut butter until well blended.
Pour half of the mixture over ice cream.
Sprinkle with half the nuts; repeat layering.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes for easy cutting.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls to fit 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with mixture of next 3 ingredients.
Chop fine 6 fresh vegetables and sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Use radishes, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green or red peppers, mushrooms, black or green olives, onions or whatever you like.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Grease cookie sheets with margarine.
In large pan, add Karo and sugar.
Cook until they come to a boil.
Boil only 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and cereal. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Let cool.

title: corn green bean casserole
directions: Mix
beans and corn; put into greased baking dish.
Mix soup, cheese
and sour cream; pour over beans and corn.
Bake 30 minutes
at
Mix
crackers,
margarine and almonds; spread over casserole.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: clams casino
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter and Worcestershire sauce. Place on top of clams along with the bacon.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli with oyster sauce
directions: In wok, put oil and coat broccoli first.
Add a mixture of sugar, salt and water.
When done, put in oyster sauce.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in lime and water solution.
Let stand 24 hours.
Rinse well; let soak for 3 hours in cold water.
Drain well.
Make syrup of sugar, spices, vinegar and salt.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Boil 35 minutes over slow heat. Put in sterilized glass jars and seal.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until sugar is dissolved.
Beat whites until they are very stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until sugar is dissolved.
Mix the whites and yolks.
Whip the cream and stir cream and milk into the egg mixture.
Very slowly, add bourbon and rum.
Stir well.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Saute sausage, bell pepper, onion and celery.
Drain off fat. To water add soup mix and rice.
Cook 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In well greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, and milk until partially blended.
Put butter on top in center of dish.
Put dish in microwave on high for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Not important for butter to be completely melted.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined dish.
Chill for 1 hour. Makes 20 squares.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix everything, except broccoli, together.
Then add broccoli.
Serve as hot dip or over ham and English muffins as a main course.

title: slush
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Mix all other ingredients. Add enough water to make 2 gallons.
Freeze.
Stir twice within 24 hours.
If frozen hard, take out a couple of hours before serving.

title: favorite cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add milk, eggs and oil, combined. Combine lightly and pour into shallow, buttered pan, 8 x 8-inch. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: red beans and rice(spanish style)
directions: Saute onion, olives, capers and bacon or ham in oil until onion is tender.
Add beans, tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Season to taste.
Add jalapeno pepper (whole) and cook until beans are real tender, removing pepper when beans become as hot as you want, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over Spanish Rice.

title: cherry chocolate cake(microwave)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix by hand until thoroughly combined. Pour into a buttered microwave Bundt pan that has been sprinkle with cocoa powder. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes. Test for doneness with toothpick. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, orange segments, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.

title: crab spread
directions: Beat together by hand until blended. Sprinkle some Cheddar on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Combine all dry ingredients until evenly mixed.
Pour into jar.
Add wet ingredients.
Shake well and chill.
Yield: 3/4 cup dressing.

title: donna blocker's chili
directions: Cook garlic, onion, red peppers, jalapeno peppers, bell pepper, salt and pepper together with meats.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and juice and tomato soup.
Add bratwurst and remaining ingredients.
May be served with rice or hot dogs.
Enjoy!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add water and next 8 ingredients.
Mix corn meal and flour to a paste and add to meat mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or plain.

title: green bean soup
directions: In a soup pot, melt butter and saute onions and pepperoni until warm through.
Stir in paprika.
Add green beans and potatoes and cover with enough water to make a soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: applesauce spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat applesauce, brown sugar, oil and eggs in large mixing bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 1 minute.
Stir in baking mix, pumpkin pie spice and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserts clean.
Cool and frost with Browned Butter Glaze; cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Blend in a 6 ounce package of chocolate chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, then sugar.
Mix.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Fold in carrots.
Pour into angel food-type cake pan.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water to cover in a medium saucepan 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine onion and next 5 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Stir in squash. Spoon squash mixture into a 2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: baked salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bake 30 minutes at 250° in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix together rest of ingredients, all but Cool Whip.
Pour over top of cake mixture. Top with Cool Whip and chill.
Good as dessert also!!!

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain all liquid.
Combine all other ingredients with spinach.
Mix with hand mixture for a creamier dip.
If possible, refrigerate for one day before serving.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make stuffing according to directions. Add onions to boiling water. Let stuffing cool. Mix all ingredients together. Place in buttered 11 x 13 baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheddar broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, cheese and onion. Combine the mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar; pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat.
Refrigerate for at lease 4 hours.
Just before serving, stir in the bacon.

title: cherry freeze salad
directions: Mix and freeze in muffin cups.

title: cherry salad
directions: Heat sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Mash cream cheese and cut up cherries until smooth. Mix the gelatine and pineapple mixture; blend in cream cheese mixture.
Cool until it starts to thicken.
Blend in whipped cream and chill.

title: tomatoes stuffed with spinach pesto
directions: Remove cores from tomatoes.
Place tomatoes, stem side down. Cut each tomato to resemble a flower by cutting into 8 wedges almost through to the bottom.
Combine spinach, basil, cheese, walnuts, oil, salt, garlic powder and black pepper in container of electric blender or food processor.
Process until smooth.
Place in bowl and stir in rice.
Spoon into tomato flowers.

title: honey mustard wings
directions: In large bowl, mix soup mix, honey and mustard.
Set aside. Cut wings at joint and discard tips.
Add to mixture.
Toss to coat.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done, turning once.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: rocky road dessert pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Can also use a 12 x 12-inch cake tin or small rectangular cake tin.
Reserve 1 2/3 cups lightly packed cake mix (dry).
Beat remaining cake mix, water, oil and eggs in medium bowl on low speed, scraping bowl often, for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium, scraping bowl frequently 2 minutes.
Spread in pie plate.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: dressing
directions: Cook turkey giblets in approximately 2-quart pan of water. Cut up giblets when cooked.
Tear cornbread and biscuits in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour giblet broth over mixture until it holds together well.
Stuff turkey and cook according to turkey directions.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder. Set aside. Beat butter, adding sugar until mixed well. To butter mixture, add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla. Slowly blend flour mixture into dough.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out dough to about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with desired cutters. Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Decorate with vanilla frosting, if desired.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: grandma borst's beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot for 4 hours on high and 2 hours on low.

title: vegetable party dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate several hours. Serve with chips, crackers or raw vegetables.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fruity party punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, ginger ale and sugar in punch bowl.
Fill bowl with as much of the fruit punch as it will hold, but leave room for the ice.
Fills large punch bowl.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in water and continue to stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Add strawberry Jell-O and mix until dissolved.
Mix glaze with strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with butter; blend until smooth.
Pour over cereal; mix well.
Pour powdered sugar over mixture.
Cover and shake well.

title: pocket stew
directions: Put ground beef (1/4 pound), carrots, potatoes and onions in four individually wrapped heavy-duty foil.
Bring foil up and over.
Roll and secure edges so moisture does not escape.
Bake at 325° for one hour, or until done.
Makes four servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain well.
Separate rolls and arrange on 12-inch pizza pan to cover.
Spoon sausage on crust. Top with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and spices. Pour on pizza.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf and return to the oven.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: sherried beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 4 hours or longer.
Or can be cooked in a crock-pot on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: low calorie meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, garlic salt and bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water in a small bowl; blend into beef mixture.
Shape into balls using 1 tablespoons beef mixture per ball.
Arrange in single layer on broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from source of heat for 5 minutes, turning once.
Combine tomato sauce and 1 cup water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add meatballs to sauce and return to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer for 10 minutes longer to allow sauce to thicken slightly.
Skim off excess fat. Yields 4 servings at 253 calories per serving.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Melt butter. Add cocoa. Stir. Add remaining ingredients and heat until smooth. Add more milk, if necessary.

title: fanned apricot coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a baking sheet, set aside.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With a pastry blender, or 2 knives, cut in cream cheese, butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse peas. Stir in milk.
On lightly floured board, knead dough gently 20 times.
Place dough on waxed paper.
Roll out to a 12 inch by 8 inch rectangle.
Turn rectangle onto the greased baking sheet. Spread apricot preserves lengthwise to cover 2/3 of the rectangle. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Fold the third of the rectangle without preserves over the center.
Fold over again, making 3 layers of dough and 2 layers of filling.
Seal edges.
From folded edge, cut dough into 1 inch slices to within 1 inch of opposite side; twist strips so that cut side is up.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove coffeecake from baking sheet.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
If desired, drizzle glaze over top.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Saute garlic, onions and pepper in margarine until transparent.
Add flour, salt, pepper, soups, pimentos and meat. Cook egg noodles; drain.

title: coconut cream delight cake
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions. Cool for 10 minutes, then poke many holes in cake with a large meat fork.
Mix cream of coconut with Eagle Brand milk together.
Pour slowly over top of cake and allow it to seep into holes.
Use a spoon to help spread and control the flow.
Top cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: First, simmer raisins in small saucepan with lid for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Melt Crisco in 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, oatmeal, then eggs and vanilla.
Measure the hot raisin liquid into a cup.
Stir in soda and add.
Drain any remaining liquid from raisins.
Mix in flour sifted with salt, then stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop from spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mexican bread
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together except for peppers, hamburger meat and cheese.
Pour half into skillet. In remaining half, add peppers, hamburger meat and cheese.
Pour over first half and smooth.
Bake at 350° degrees until brown (1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes).

title: inez watson's stir-n-roll pastry
directions: Pour liquid (all at once) into dry mixture.
Stir until it forms a ball.
Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Fit into pie plate and prick with fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cool, then add desired filling.

title: lazy day dessert
directions: Mix everything but cool whip.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a microwave bowl.
Place butter on top.
Place in microwave oven for 3 minutes on High or until butter melts.
Remove and stir in 1 cup peanut butter; stir thoroughly.
It will set quickly.
Pour into a buttered pan. Cool.
No need to refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and dump in peanuts.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until reaches hard-crack stage (285° to 310°). I remove it from the heat at exactly 300° on candy thermometer. Dump in butter, salt and soda. Stir a little to reduce foam. Pour out quickly onto greased cookie sheet. Smooth with the back of spoon a little bit. Cool completely. Break into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all together and serve with seafood.

title: praline cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by spoon.
Let cool until firm.

title: quick mix biscuits
directions: Measure flour into bowl.
Pour in milk and oil.
Mix together. Put dough on floured board; knead several times.
Makes into biscuits. Bake 15 or 20 minutes in 350° to 400° oven.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture along with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: equal apple pie(31% calorie reduction from traditional pie)
directions: Roll 1/2 pastry on floured surface into a circle 1-inch larger than inverted pie pan. Ease pastry into pan.

title: orange salad
directions: When the first 3 ingredients are partially set, add the oranges.

title: chicken with chinese 5 spice
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken.
Mix all ingredients, except scallions and cilantro.
Rub chicken with some of the sauce.
Chop scallions in 2-inch lengths.
Stuff scallions and cilantro in cavity.
Pour in the rest of the sauce.
Roast at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until juices run clear when poked.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: frozen cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise; add pineapple and mix.
Add cherries and whipped cream.
Pour into tray and freeze 2 hours. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise and a cherry on top of each square.

title: s'mores
directions: Spread peanut butter on half a graham cracker.
Top with marshmallow.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until marshmallow is golden brown.
Top with other half of graham cracker.
Press gently.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Combine green pepper, tomatoes, celery, onion and salt.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Drain.
Add sugar, mustard seed, dry mustard and vinegar.
Let stand another 24 hours. Transfer to freezer containers, cover and refrigerate or freeze.

title: goldie, gourmet chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken breasts with garlic powder and onion powder; salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap each chicken breast around a broccoli stalk and secure with wooden picks.
Arrange in baking dish, laying a slice of cheese on each breast.
Combine crumbs with melted margarine and spread mixture over cheese slices.
Mix soup with 1/2 to 3/4 cup water and pour over chicken.
Cover dish with foil, making a few small slits in the foil.
Bake 1 hour, uncover dish and bake 10 minutes longer. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: heart healthy cucumber spread
directions: Grate cucumbers and press dry with paper towels.
Add other ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs in saucepan; when done, peel and separate yolk from egg white. Place yolk in good size bowl and mash.
Chop in egg white; add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes and lettuce. Mix well.
Serve on its own or make a sandwich with the lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: quick, easy dumplings
directions: Cook chicken; remove from pan (keep from sticking).
Add milk and butter to broth.
Tear biscuits in about 10 pieces.
After adding all biscuits, add chicken and salt and pepper to taste. Cook about 15 minutes.
Let set with lid on about 10 minutes. Enjoy.
Very good left over.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Keep in a cool place.
Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add coloring and cocoa.
Sift flour and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Do not beat soda and vinegar! Sprinkle soda on batter, then pour vinegar over batter mixture and stir well until well blended.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon thoroughly but do not allow to crisp.
Drain on paper towels and chop into small pieces.
Place vinegar, bacon fat, olive oil and chives in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, add scallions and sugar and return to a boil.
Add bacon and pour over the spinach.
Toss well and serve at once.

title: chicken rice
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken in white
directions: Put oil in 6-quart pot.
Add chicken breast halves, cover and steam until cooked 3/4 way through.
Add all the seasonings and water.
It should cover the chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup to ingredients in pot.
Cover with lid and simmer for 2 hours.

title: italian nachos
directions: Arrange tortilla chips on plate.
Spoon pizza sauce over top. Add pizza toppings as desired.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Microwave 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Place crescent rolls in bottom of a pie pan (like a star). The narrow edges should hang out of the pan.
Press the fat ends together to cover the bottom of the pan.
Cream the cream cheese. Add powdered sugar.
Mix well, then spread in pie pan.
Bring your narrow edges towards middle of pan.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar on top.
Bake at 275° for 1/2 hour.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on package.
Melt garlic cheese and margarine over low heat.
Mix into cooked grits.
Blend in the eggs and milk.
Mix into the grits.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Mix beef, crumbs, salt, pepper and onions.
Shape into patties and brown in skillet.
Pour mushroom soup mixed with water over patties and simmer 45 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill jars with small cucumbers.
Put 1 leaf and a sprig of dill in each jar.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Pour in jars and seal.

title: chicken with ginger and garbanzo beans
directions: Do not skimp on the ginger.
Serve with a starch such as bulgur or brown rice.

title: mawmaw's banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Cool slightly.
In a large bowl, place a layer of wafers and bananas on top of wafers.
Cover with pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding on top.
Put three wafers on top in triangle design.

title: party beef
directions: Combine chili sauce, sugar, salt, vinegar and seasoned salt. Pour over meat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. (Marinate meat in Pyrex glass pan.)
Place meat in roasting pan. Pour over marinade; cover with celery leaves and onions.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours (1 hour per pound).
Baste often.
Serve in strained marinade.
This recipe may be prepared 2 days in advance or frozen.

title: blender broccoli soup
directions: Partially thaw broccoli; break in small chunks.
Place in blender container with 1/2 cup of the milk.
Blend until broccoli is very fine.
Add remaining milk, cream, instant minced onions, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth, 45 to 60 seconds.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve topped with dollops of dairy sour cream and snipped parsley or chives.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: bruschetta con pomodori
directions: Cut bread in 1/4-inch slices on a diagonal; toast on oven rack at 350° for 10 minutes; flip at 5 minutes.
Cut tomatoes in half and push seeds out with your thumb.
Dice the tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes with garlic and basil, then olive oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture on toasted bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to 350° oven for 15 to 30 seconds.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Place on pan.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spice cider cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir together dry ingredients.
Combine cider and milk. Thoroughly blend flour into creamed mixture alternately with cider mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar-free cherry pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup cherry juice with cornstarch and salt.
Combine with cherries and cook until thickened, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sweetener.
Pour into pie shell.
Serve with prepared whipped topping if desired.

title: soup beans
directions: Place ham in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water and put on high heat.
Remove bad beans and extraneous matter from dried beans.
Pour beans in pot with ham and water.
Bring to boil. When it comes to a boil, cover and simmer for several hours, until beans are tender.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour. Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onion and green pepper rings and garlic to skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add chicken to sauce. Cover.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are fork-tender.
Serve over rice.

title: top-of-stove candied sweet potatoes
directions: Put sugar and water in a frying pan.
Stir; let it boil 5 minutes.
This makes a syrup.
Add margarine and salt; stir.
Wash and peel sweet potatoes.
Cut in slices, about 1/2-inch thick. Cut the slices in strips.
Put sweet potatoes in the syrup; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until sweet potatoes are tender.

title: coconut pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in condensed milk, whipped topping and coconut.
Chill until set.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with sugar, Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Pour into pie shell and top with broken pieces of peanuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Crumble crackers coarsely and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Place bite-size chicken over cracker mixture.
Mix sour cream, hot broth and chicken soup until smooth.
Pour over chicken and crackers.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix Jell-O and cheese.
Add fruit.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: ground beef stew
directions: In casserole dish, layer first 6 ingredients.
Mix reserved pea juice with tomato soup.
Pour over ground beef.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (until vegetables are soft).

title: clam fritters
directions: Pour milk slowly into dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth and fold in eggs.
Add clams.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Fry one side until brown, then turn and do the other side.

title: cowboy baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix flour, shortening, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl, mashing together until a granular consistency, then stop.
Pour in water and fold into layers.
Put on floured surface; flatten to 2 inches thick and cut into 2 1/2-inch circles with water glass.
Place onto greased and floured biscuit pan and cook at 325° until blonde color.
Check middle of biscuit for non-doughy center and enjoy.

title: cream of parisian soup
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in water until blended.
Melt butter in large pan and fry celery and onion.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Crush bouillon cubes; add to margarine/flour.
Add vegetables, ham, salt, pepper, Accent| and celery seed.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: no-bake-chocolate-treats
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cocoa, vanilla and coffee.
Add oats and mix with wooden spoon until well blended.
Shape into bite-sized balls and roll in coconut.
Chill and keep stored in refrigerator covered until ready to serve.

title: zucchini sausage skillet
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch pieces.
Shape sausage into 16 meatballs and brown in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Add tomato and serve.

title: broken glass dessert
directions: When jello is chilled and firm, cut into cubes. Bring pineapple juice to a boil.
Add Knox gelatine water.
Mix well and chill until syrupy.
Mix crumbs, sugar and melted butter together. Use half of crumb mix to line bottom of pan.
Reserve other half for topping. Combine Cool Whip with pineapple mix in a large bowl. Fold in the jello cubes. Spread over crumb crust.
Top with reserved crumb mix and chill.

title: bruce the moose venison recipe
directions: Add margarine, garlic and wine together in skillet until melted.
Add sliced venison.
Saute on one side for 8 to 12 minutes.
Turn meat.
Place onions and peppers on top.
Cover skillet and simmer until almost all liquid is evaporated.

title: cheesy barbecue biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8-inch round cake pan. Separate can of biscuits into 10 and place in pans, sides touching each other.
Brush biscuits with barbecue sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Place on round platter; spread 2 inches from edge.
Spread a layer of lettuce, cheese and tomatoes over top of creamed mixture. Surround with tortilla chips.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Put 1 tablespoon dill seed into each of the 6 quart jars. Boil water, salt and vinegar.
Pour into jars while bubbling. Seal.

title: ranch bread
directions: Combine butter or margarine and Hidden Valley.
Spread on top of French bread.
Place bread under broiler until crispy and golden brown.

title: applesauce nut loaf
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in applesauce and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add white and brown sugar.
Pour in mixing bowl.
Add one egg at a time alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix and pour into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hamburger or dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients and flour to handle.
Knead down after first rising.
Let rise again.
Put in bread pans at 10:00 P.M. and bake in morning at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix sour cream and egg yolks.
Combine all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with your favorite meringue.

title: capellini with clams
directions: In skillet, saute garlic, shallots and onion in olive oil over low heat.
When translucent, add clams and mix well.
Then add tomatoes.
Season to taste and cook approximately 5 minutes.

title: shrewsbury cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and 1 egg.
Blend thoroughly. Add other eggs, beating very thoroughly after each.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 350°.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Place egg and crackers in small bowl; crush and mix well.
Add A.1. sauce and garlic powder; set aside.
Mix hamburger and onion.

title: mother's butterscotch pie
directions: Melt sugar (low setting) in skillet, stirring until brown (medium).
Heat milk and add to sugar.
Stir until all sugar is melted.
Mix egg yolks with cornstarch and water mixture.
Add to milk and sugar mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.
Place in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: harlequin pie
directions: Make pie crust.
Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter the size that will fit the mini cupcake pans to cover the bottom and sides. Fill 3/4 full with filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: "maggie's chili"
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder to taste.
Stir in 1 to 2 tablespoons flour, depending on how much grease the hamburger makes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 55 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.
The pan should be a greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch).
Set to cool on a rack before slicing.

title: extra light beer biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter or drop in greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° until browned, about 15 minutes.

title: nine layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together and spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle Italian dressing mix over mixture.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Serves 6.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco. Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder. Add alternately with milk. Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk over low heat in double boiler. Mix cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk. Pat 1/2 of cake mixture in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.

title: green beans with onion rings casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix soup with canned milk and pour over beans.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli noodle soup
directions: Cook egg noodles for 4 minutes; drain and set aside.
Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add water.
Boil and add bouillon cubes. Boil.
Add milk and simmer.
Add broccoli.
Add cheese until melted.
Add noodles.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole, spread half the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture. Cover with remaining noodles.
Put hamburger mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth and blended; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until filling is firm.
Let stand on cake rack until cold.
Spread with sour cream; chill 1 hour.

title: festive fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve on ice.
Contains 41 calories.

title: lemon bars
directions: Crust:
Mix 2 cups flour, margarine and powdered sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian veggies(low-fat)
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in nonstick frypan and saute vegetables (first 6 ingredents) until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick as you want.
Serve as side vegetable or as sauce for pasta with Parmesan cheese.

title: western pork chops
directions: Melt butter, add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Remove chops.
Add green pepper and onion.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Return chops to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise together and set aside. Mix broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese together.
Add dressing and toss together.

title: cheesy potato wedges
directions: In a plastic food storage bag combine Parmesan, onion salt and paprika.
Add potatoes; close bag.
Shake until coated.
Arrange potatoes in a 2-quart square microwave-safe dish.
Set aside 1/2 teaspoon of the Parmesan coating.
Cook potatoes, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes; give dish a full turn.
Cook for 2 to 4 minutes more or until tender and hot.
In a 1-cup glass measuring cup heat margarine or butter on High until melted.
Carefully stir in reserved coating; pour over potatoes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: First spray a pan with cooking spray and scramble the Egg Beaters.
Set aside.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Melt yeast in water and then add other ingredients and stir well.
Let stand unrefrigerated for 24 hours in a quart jar with lid loose.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients as listed except cheese. Add 2/3 of the cheese to the batter. Pour into a greased 10-inch skillet; sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's swedish torte
directions: Work 1 cup sugar and eggs together real good until creamy.
Add butter or lard and mix well.
Work ingredients together with flour real good, as there lies the secret of good results.
Separate dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll out and bake in 4 oblong pans. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine over low heat or in microwave oven.
Add peanut butter and stir until mixed well. Dump Crispix in large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over cereal. Mix well.
Sprinkle a little powdered sugar into a large brown paper grocery bag.
Pour cereal mixture into bag.
Add one half powdered sugar over cereal and shake well.
Add the rest of the sugar and shake bag again.
Store in a large plastic bowl in freezer or refrigerator.

title: sweet kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and rinse well.
Drain and squeeze out all water. Combine all other ingredients and add to kraut.
Marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Bake for 1 hour in greased loaf pan at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs; blend well. Add 4 eggs; beat well.
Add flour, lemon juice and sour cream. Add vanilla last.
Pour into 11-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 65 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not open oven door.
Turn oven off and wait 30 minutes with door closed.
Open door and let sit in oven for 30 minutes.
Take out and let cool.
Wait 24 hours before serving.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape, slice and boil carrots in salted water until just crisply done.
Drain; save 1/2 cup liquid.
Place carrots in greased 2-quart casserole.

title: autumn apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Then add butter or margarine, egg, apples and pecans or walnuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper, diced onions and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Sprinkle salt on; broil until lightly browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Combine remaining ingredients, including pineapple juice, and pour over chicken. Bake in 375 degree oven uncovered for 45 minutes or until chicken is browned.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add soda to cold water and combine with sugar mixture, along with salt and vanilla, then add flour and mix.
It will be quite heavy.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: applesauce brown nut cake
directions: Cream applesauce and sugar. Add beaten egg whites, one at a time, beating after each. Mix all dry ingredients together (reserve 1 cup for dredging fruits and nuts). Add to creamed mixture. Add mashed bananas, dredged fruit, preserves and nuts to the mixture. Mix well. Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour or longer if needed at 350°.
Always check after 1 hour to see if done, if not, place a piece of aluminum foil over top of pan and cook 20 to 30 minutes longer. Since this cake freezes well, it can be stored for future use.

title: magic peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 minutes or until chips melt.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: cloud nine cream
directions: Place cream cheese in a small bowl and beat until creamy. Gradually add the 1/4 cup reserved pineapple syrup and beat until light and smooth.
Prepare the whipped topping mix according to package directions.
Fold in the cream cheese mixture, sugar, nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Cover and chill three hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook
first
3	ingredients to soft ball stage.
Remove from stove
and	add next 3 ingredients, stirring constantly, until well
blended.
Spread evenly into square pan or baking dish (buttered).

title: amaretto-hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup for other uses. Combine fruits in a large bowl; set aside. Combine bananas and lemon juice. Toss lightly. Add to other fruit mixture. Layer half each of fruit mixture and macaroon crumbs in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sliced almonds and dot with 3 tablespoons butter. Repeat second half. Pour Amaretto evenly over fruit mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining almonds. Stir before serving. Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spread cooked chicken pieces in
large casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Place sliced cheese over chicken and onion. Crumble 6 ounces of chips over cheese. Blend Ro-Tel and cream soups and pour over casserole.
Crumble 6 ounces tortilla chips over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil. Bake another 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: frank's old fashioned parched corn
directions: Cut fresh sweet corn off cob. Melt butter in frying pan and pour in some dry corn. Put a lid on and cook on top of the stove or put in the oven.
Stir frequently and let it brown. Sprinkle with salt (pepper is optional).
Corn should not be piled too thick.
May repeat, using 1/2 the corn.
Serve hot. Great while watching T.V.
Will serve 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions; set aside. Combine peanut butter, sugar and milk; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of peanut butter mixture in crust, then spread pudding mixture over this.
Next spread remaining peanut butter mixture over pudding. Chill for about 30 minutes. Top with Cool Whip and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: ham-broccoli rolls
directions: Microwave broccoli until tender. Place margarine in bowl and microwave until hot. Stir flour, horseradish, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Add pineapple juice and milk; stir until blended. Add egg and blend. Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes depending upon microwave.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add next 4 ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine other ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Bring water to a boil; add salt and corn meal.
Stir as you are adding corn meal with a wire whip.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes (add more water for thinner mush).
Serve with milk and sugar or honey.
Pour leftover mush in pan and let set overnight.
Slice and fry mush.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Combine sea stix or crabmeat imitation and celery in bowl. Mix in mayonnaise and onions. Add salt, pepper and lemon juice. Chill for 2 hours. Serve on lettuce bed. Makes 4 servings.

title: sheena's grandma's delicous chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and butter; add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix all ingredients together, add chips and nuts.
Take a teaspoonful and roll into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together and line baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, lightly browned.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, vanilla, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil until thick.
Pour mixture into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks; spread over pie.
Bake until brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Brown onions and bell pepper with bacon. Add rice, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: dixie's lemon sandwich filling
directions: Mix lemon juice, butter, sugar and egg together.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add chopped raisins and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Spread on bread.

title: bar-b-que sauce
directions: Heat margarine, vinegar, peppers and salt and it is ready to use.
Baste chicken during cooking.
Does not burn like a tomato type sauce.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Using 1/2 of each ingredient, put a layer of chips, peas and tuna.
Mix soup and milk and heat.
Pour 1/2 of milk mixture over layers.
Repeat layers and end with a few crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and 3/4 package of taco mix (no water). Set aside to cool. Chop lettuce, tomatoes and olives. Crush Doritos. Mix meat, lettuce, tomatoes, olives and Doritos together. Add dressing (1/4 package taco seasoning, taco sauce and Thousand Island dressing) and mix well.

title: chicken chunks
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Beat eggs and mix with water, flour, sesame seed and salt to make a batter.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Dip chicken
in
batter
and fry in hot oil until golden brown (about
5 minutes), turning once.
Drain on a paper towel.
Serves
Good
served
with
sweet and sour sauce.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until brown, drain and add salt and pepper.
Spread in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk, and baking mix until smooth.
Pour over beef.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese, and bake 5 to 8 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
