Mix Wyler's or Lipton dry chicken noodle soup mix well with 2 1/2 cups of water.
Cook Minute rice according to directions on package.
Mix together with browned ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: honey creme dressing
directions: Whip or mash cream cheese with salt, honey and sour cream in small bowl.
Serve with salad.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Boil together
2 Cup boiling water and tea bags. Mix together next 5 ingredients and freeze.
In a 9 oz. glass put in half slush and half ginger ale or 7-up.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients altogether.
Mix the sour cream, Miracle Whip and garlic salt.
Mix altogether.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remix before serving.

title: grape leaves
directions: In large bowl, mix well the ground lamb and the washed rice. Season with salt and pepper and the cinnamon.
Add the can of tomato sauce and mix well with hands.
Add two or three of the whole tomatoes which you have squeezed between your hands and some of the tomato juice from the can until the mixture is somewhat soft and pliable.
Reserve the remaining tomatoes and juice.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Blend brown sugar with flour and salt.
Separate eggs and set aside the whites for meringue.
Beat yolks and blend with evaporated milk.
Add to sugar mixture and cook, stirring constantly.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Spread meringue on top. Good!

title: fresh fruit with dressing
directions: Make melon balls.
Cut up strawberries, peaches, etc.
Combine all fruit in large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine yogurt and honey.
Pour over fruit and stir gently to coat all fruit. Refrigerate.

title: butterhorns(mothers)
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Knead 5 minutes.
Set to raise.
When double in size, roll.

title: thirteen bean soup
directions: Rinse and pick over beans.
Put in a 4 or 5-quart Dutch oven with 3 cups water.
Cover, bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat; let soak 1 hour.
Drain; add 8 cups water and the seasonings.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender but still firm.
Uncover, increase heat to medium-low and boil gently, stirring occasionally, 45 to 60 minutes until soup is slightly thickened.
Discard bay leaves. Makes 10 cups.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine onion, cauliflower and broccoli flowerets.
Mix dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate 4 hours or longer.

title: snickerwoodles(for the kids)
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl.
Cream the 3/4 cup of sugar and the butter with a wooden spoon.
Beat in egg and vanilla.

title: vienna torte
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Combine sugar, flour and baking soda in a large bowl.
In a saucepan combine butter, water and cocoa. Bring to boil.
Add the chocolate mixture to the flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla. Pour into a greased and flowered 15 x 10 x 1 inch jellyroll pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Allow cake to cool in pan.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add rest of sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating in.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt; add to flour and add to creamed egg mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk and mix.
Add to mixture along with the flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour in preheated oven.
Can be frozen.

title: meatless lentil soup
directions: Cover and simmer lentils, water and salt for 3 to 4 hours. Saute garlic, onion, celery and carrots.
Add to lentils after 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, wine, vinegar, sherry, lemon juice, brown sugar and seasonings after 3 1/2 hours.
Cook 30 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6 generously.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add water, a little at a time, until onion and meat are done.
Put soup mix in.
Add water, about 2 inches over meat, and cook down.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add rice.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: In large skillet, add olive oil; fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and crumble. Cut up cabbage; dice onion and bell pepper. Mince garlic. Add all ingredients to leftover bacon drippings and smother fry until cabbage is crispy-tender. Then add crumbled bacon. Serve while hot.

title: pasta with scallops
directions: Place margarine, milk and scallops in casserole dish. Microwave for 5 minutes, until margarine is melted and scallops are cooked.
Add peas and microwave until all is warm.
Toss lightly with your favorite pasta.
Serve warm.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Slowly add flour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot mexican cider
directions: Combine cider and juice in pan.
Heat to simmer.
Add rest. Heat through.
Serve and enjoy.
Serves 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins before adding to filling.
Mix next six ingredients together and cook in microwave until thick.
Add raisins and put in cooked pie shell.
Put meringue on pie and bake until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and then dice.
Add all ingredients except for 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corned beef and mushroom pate
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until well browned; cool. Beat corned beef and sour cream until well mixed.
Add mushroom mixture, mustard, pepper and horseradish.
Pack in oiled 2 cup mold; chill several hours.
Unmold and garnish with parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix bread, eggs, onion and celery seasoning.
Stir in broth. Put in black pepper.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour, until brown.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir until smooth; add all other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream puffs
directions: Fill cream puffs with your favorite filling such as chicken salad, ham salad, chocolate pudding or Cream Cheese Filling (see recipe).

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook with stirring to hard ball stage or 250°.
Wipe crystals from side of pan with damp cloth or paper towel.
Remove from heat.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla. Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper or pour into pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: mark twain's sweet mince cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; combine brandy and cream.
Add dry ingredients and brandy-cream mixture alternately to margarine mixture, beginning and ending with dries. In a small bowl, combine mincemeat and 2 tablespoons flour until blended.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, until cake is golden brown.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn cake out onto dish.

title: paccs(principal's apple cereal caramel squares)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine apples, cereal, peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix well in a large bowl.
In a small saucepan over low heat, combine milk and unwrapped caramels.
Stir until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss gently to coat.
Press in greased pan.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Great for bake sales and lunch boxes.
tags: bite size crisp rice cereal squares

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until thick. Add everything else and process in ice cream freezer.
Your favorite fruit may be added for variation.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl (I add some chicken broth to make it a little more moist).
Pour into 3-quart baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
You can put some grated cheese on top, just before it finishes cooking if you like.
Freezes well.

title: moist coffee chocolate cake
directions: This is a very thin batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: taco salad(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion. Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until meat loses its pink color, stirring to break up meat after half the cooking time. Drain. Stir in beans, water and taco seasoning.
Microwave, uncovered, at 50% (Medium) for 10 to 13 minutes or until thick and bubbly, stirring once.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and green pepper in salad bowl while meat and beans cook. Spoon mixture over lettuce. Top with cheeses, then corn chips.
Serve immediately with chili sauce or taco sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: volunteer taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; remove from heat and drain off excessive liquid and fat.
Add onion, powder, seasoning, and tomato sauce; mix and set aside.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine sour cream and cottage cheese.
Set aside.

Place half the crushed chips in a bottom of 2 1/2- quart casserole dish that has been coated with non-stick vegetable spray. Add enough meat mixture to cover chips, then cover with half the sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with half the shredded cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes, until cheese melts and casserole is heat through.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt stick of butter with cream cheese over low heat.
Add crabmeat and stir.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Place into chafing dish.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Enough for a party of 10.

title: guacamole
directions: Pit and peel avocados.
Mash pulp in bowl and stir in remaining ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Cover top with a thin layer of mayonnaise to keep mixture from darkening; refrigerate. Stir well before serving with tostados for dipping.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: 6 layer casserole
directions: Stir together the tomato juice, basil, oregano, parsley and Worcestershire sauce. Set aside. In a 2qt. casserole dish layer the rice, meat, onion rings, bell pepper and carrot.
Pour the liquid over the top. Sprinkle with grated cheese, cover, bake for about 2 hours at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4.

title: sweet milk johnnycake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Dissolve baking soda in cream or Crisco. Mix together.
Add milk.
Add blackberries (if desired).
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken with vegetables
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish with thick pieces towards outside of dish. Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder, paprika and pepper.
Layer celery over top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 10 minutes, turn dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Layer green pepper and onion over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Arrange mushrooms and tomatoes over top. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: party wieners
directions: In crock-pot, mix jelly and mustard.
Add hot dogs.
Simmer until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Lay peaches in bottom of 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of peaches.
Dot with oleo.
Sprinkle on nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until cobbler is golden brown.
Good served with ice cream.

title: baked chicken with soup
directions: Season chicken inside and outside with seasoning.
Spread soup over chicken.
Bake covered in roaster or Pyrex dish until chicken is tender.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken soup

title: woody's fresh tomato salsa
directions: This recipe is prepared in layers in a 9-inch pie plate as follows:

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Cut shortening into flour with a pastry blender.
Store in airtight container.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add beer and egg. Dip fish or chicken and deep fry.

title: russian chocolate
directions: Scald chocolate drink; remove from heat and add hot coffee. Whip the cream with sugar.
Add 1/2 of whipped cream to chocolate and coffee and whisk until frothy.
Serve hot, topped with remainder of whipped cream.

title: checkerboard cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Divide batter in half.
Add melted chocolate to one-half of batter; mix well.
Line three 9-inch round checkerboard cake pans with greased waxed paper.
Grease sides of pan.
Place checkerboard divider rings into one prepared pan.
Spoon one third of chocolate batter into center and outer rings; spoon one third of white cake batter into middle ring, filling half full (a pastry bag may be used to pipe batter into rings).
Smooth batter with a small spatula. Carefully remove checkerboard rings.
Rinse rings and dry thoroughly before placing in next pan.
Repeat procedure with second pan.
Spoon white batter into the center and outer rings of third pan, filling half full.
Spoon chocolate batter into middle ring, filling half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans and let cool completely.
Spread Chocolate Butter Frosting between layers, placing the white outer layer in the center.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef-in-casserole
directions: In large skillet combine first 7 ingredients.
Cook over low flame 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix noodles with sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
In a greased 3-quart casserole dish, arrange meat and noodle mixture in alternate layers with 1 cup grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Increase meat to 2 pounds if desired.

title: two blueberry pies
directions: Bake pie crust with one cup pecans to each crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Put half of cream cheese mixture on top of each pie.
Then put half of blueberry pie filling to each pie.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill for about 2 hours.
Then serve.

title: my own orange (lemon) pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, put the butter and white sugar; cream with an electric beater.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add the vanilla; mix well.
Alternate the flour with 1 cup of liquid. Add the grated lemon or orange rind.
Beat well.
Pour into a 10-inch heavy Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch aluminum pan (greased with butter).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, or until done. Test with a toothpick.
When cool, this cake can be plain, sprinkled with powdered sugar or lightly frosted.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
When totally mixed, make small 1-inch balls.
Take waxed paper and cover with cinnamon. Roll your ball into the cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: cantonese casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions, celery and beef and cook until meat is brown.
Add soy sauce, soups and vegetables.
Turn mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with noodles.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lavender sugar
directions: In food processor with chopping blade, process sugar and lavender until flowers are finely chopped.
Store in jar or airtight container.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine sugar and water in small saucepan and boil for 3 minute.
With steel cutting blade in place, add cream to the mixing container of the food processor.
Process until a very thick whipped cream forms, about 1 minute.
Transfer to a 2-quart decorative mold.
Without washing mixing container, reinsert steel cutting blade and add chocolate pieces.
Process, using on and off touch control, for 15 to 20 seconds.
Continue processing and gradually pour in hot syrup, rum and egg yolks.
Using a spatula or small whisk, scrape chocolate mixture over whipped cream and fold together.
Place mold in freezer for 6 hours.
Unmold and garnish with toasted almonds, if desired.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: easy chicken rival soup
directions: Cut egg in flour until small pea size.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Slowly stir in rivals in hot broth.
Turn heat down to low; simmer until thickened and rivals are done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick n easy shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients with mixer.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini squash bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in greased and floured loaf pans.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding chips and sauce just before serving.
Serve immediately.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well and form into a loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Meat Loaf: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix beef, onion, egg, tomato sauce, crackers, Worcestershire, salt and pepper and shape into a loaf. (You have to mix it with your hands.) Place in loaf pan or casserole. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Drain grease twice during cooking.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Unfold pastry crust.
Spread Dijon mustard on the inside. Place cheese in the middle.
Bring opposite corners over top of cheese to make a box.
Pinch crust to seal the sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes. Slice when ready to serve.

title: hot chinese chicken salad
directions: Roll chicken in cornstarch; heat oil in wok or frypan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Quickly brown.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add tomato, water chestnuts, mushrooms, onion and celery; stir and sprinkle with flavor enhancer.
Stir in soy sauce.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lettuce and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and combine with buttermilk.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 275°, then increase heat to 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and soak in ice water for 2 hours. Drain and add all remaining ingredients. Cook for 10 minutes. Seal in jars.

title: play dough
directions: Combine the 3 dry ingredients.
Bring the water to a full boil.
Add the oil and food coloring to the boiling water.
Take the water from the heat and add the dry ingredients, stirring until well mixed. When the mixture is cool enough to handle, put it out on the table and knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.
Plastic Cool Whip or butter containers work well.

title: kurdish soup
directions: Boil lentils until soft.
Soak eggplant in salt water.
Fry chopped onion in butter.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Cook until raw smell of eggplant is gone.
Add broth or bouillon with water. Beat flour and yogurt.
Add to the soup, then add lentils.
Add dried mint.
Can be served warm or chilled.

title: holiday baked corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Turn mixture into a well-buttered, 2-quart casserole. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until bubbly and cooked through.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil; mix well.
Add sugar, vanilla and cinnamon. Gradually add flour until all is well blended.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in well greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream the butter and the 2/3 cup confectioners sugar until fluffy. Beat in the vanilla and almond extract, then add the almonds. Stir in the flour and beat until well mixed.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in a bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, including raisins.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: First boil bow tie pasta to the directions on the box and then run under cold water.
Place in large bowl.
Then place broccoli and cauliflower in with pasta.
Then put cut up chunks of Mozzarella cheese in the mixture.
Top with Italian dressing and stir.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; thaw Cool Whip.
Mix or whip ingredients together.
Serve with any fruit (grapes, cantaloupe, watermelon, etc.) for dipping.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water until cornstarch is completely dissolved.
Add 1 cup sugar, lemon juice and blackberries and combine the mixture gently but thoroughly.
Transfer to an 8-inch cast-iron skillet.

title: beef, string beans and water chestnuts
directions: Cut beef into 1/8-inch slices.
In a glass dish, such as a 10-inch pie plate, mix hoisin, soy, sherry, cornstarch and optional chili paste.
Add meat and stir.
In non-stick skillet, heat oil on high until a drop of water dances on the surface.
Stir-fry beans, mushrooms, scallions and water chestnuts until tender, about 3 minutes.
Push vegetable mixture to top sides and stir-fry beef mixture until no longer pink inside, about 2 minutes.
Mix vegetables, meat and sauce.
Place in serving dish.
Serve with steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix well the next 5 ingredients and add to dry ingredients; blend.
Add nuts and cherries.
Shape into balls.
Roll in corn flakes.
Top each ball with 1/2 cherry.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken yum yum
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken.
Mix together soups and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Mix Stove Top dressing with dry seasoning.
Melt oleo in broth (or 1 1/2 cups water).
Add Stove Top and spread over soup layer.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sausage bits
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: First, melt margarine; mix with flour and buttermilk.

title: christmas cookies with almonds
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut butter in; knead thoroughly.
Add one egg; knead again.
Let stand, covered, in icebox for 1 hour.
Roll out as thin as possible on floured board; cut with round cutter.
Put a little beaten egg on middle of each cookie.
Add a few thin slices of almond; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixed.
Bake in medium oven until light brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Drizzle on top of melted butter.
Heat 29 ounces of peaches and 1/2 cup sugar and pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: souper enchiladas
directions: Combine soup and sour cream.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion with chili powder until tender, stirring often.
Add chicken, chilies and 2 tablespoons soup mixture.

title: chestnut wraps
directions: Wrap bacon around chestnut and secure with a toothpick. Brown in oven at 350° until bacon is crisp.
Remove and drain on a paper towel.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt chocolate and shortening together in larger saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Mix in granulated sugar, liquid brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients; spread butter evenly in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies are done. Cool slightly.
Cut into bars or squares.
Makes about 32.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on for 20 minutes.
After they boil, then run cold water on them for 5 minutes.
Set in fridge.
Dice celery, cucumbers and onion.
Also dice potato into bite size chunks.
Add 3 hard-boiled eggs to the mixture and then slice up 3 eggs for the top.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Add salt and pepper if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stand 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Frost when cooled.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with fritos Scoops or tortilla chips.

title: grandma's noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a good, stiff dough.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook meat and onions until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine brown sugar, cream of tartar, butter and corn syrup in large heavy kettle.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Stir well until coated. Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: turtles
directions: Soften caramel squares and flatten.
Place a pecan half on top of each flattened caramel square.
Fold caramel around square.

title: easy banana cream pie
directions: Melt over low heat until sugar dissolves the butter and dark brown sugar; set aside.
Mix in saucepan the flour, egg yolks, salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in brown sugar butter mixture and bring to full boil.
It should be quite thick; set aside.
Beat 3 egg whites until foamy, adding 1 tablespoon sugar per egg, until they peak.
Fill pre-baked pastry or graham crust.
Cover with meringue.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and set aside. Beat milk with pudding and orange juice. Add sour cream. Mix well. Spoon over fruit. Toss to coat. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter. Spread butter on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Good with breadsticks, French bread chunks (toasted) and crackers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and seasonings.
Add drained green beans and tomato soup; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish; spoon mashed potatoes on the outside 2 inches of the dish. Sprinkle cheese on the potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: In pot, bring water, sugar, salt and vinegar to a boil. Remove from heat.
Cool.
In large container, pour cooled liquid over cucumbers, garlic and dill.
Let stand for 1 day without a lid.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: For filling beat 4 egg yolks and eagle brand and lemon juice. Pour into a large graham cracker crust.
Beat egg white for meringue adding sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla. Brown in preheated 375° oven.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: pork tenderloin in barbecue sauce
directions: Line a loaf pan with enough foil to fold completely over tenderloins.
Place meat in foil, then place onions, sauce, garlic and pepper on top.
Fold and seal foil.
Place in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Check at 45 minutes for doneness.

title: braunschweiger party spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Great on crackers.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup, water and Minute rice.
Heat until cheese melts.
Grease a casserole dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead, refrigerated and baked for one hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Place dough in deep dish pie pan.
Place 1/2 of chips on dough. Fry ground beef; drain and simmer with taco seasoning.
Spread on top of chips, then spread sour cream over meat.
Add another layer of chips; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan in the order listed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine oleo, pudding and
milk; beat well.
Blend in 1 quart vanilla ice cream and 1/2
of
a
large
carton
of Cool Whip. Line a 9 x
13-inch
pan
with
cracker
crumbs.
Pour pudding mixture into pan
and sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Refrigerate or freeze.
If frozen, set at room temperature for 1 hour before serving.

title: green cabbage with caraway and apple
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add apples. Cook a few minutes longer.
Reduce heat.
Add salt and caraway seed, cover and cook about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips; remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles until coated with butterscotch.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups sugar and whipping cream; mix well.
Add melted butter.
Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in an iron skillet. Combine with other ingredients.
Stirring constantly, cook to soft ball stage (when a drop of icing in cold water turns to a soft ball).

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package and add oranges.
Bake as directed on the package.
Mix dry pudding mix in Cool Whip and undrained pineapple.
Frost cake and refrigerate overnight.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix melted margarine, egg and sour cream; stir in both cans of corn.
Add Jiffy mix and mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine peanut butter, eggs, butter and sugar together; mix well.
Gradually add milk, a little at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes before taking out of pan and putting on a plate.
Eat plain or lightly spread with whipped cream.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While cake is cooking, combine pudding and cream cheese.
After cake is cooled, spread mixture over cake.
Drain pineapple and put on top of pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple and top with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: garlic glazed chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in marinade or salad dressing 1 hour; broil and cut into bite-size pieces, then set aside.
Toast sesame seed 4 minutes; cool and set aside.
Combine garlic, red pepper, soy sauce, honey and vinegar in a bowl.
Heat on medium-high about 15 minutes until syrupy.
Return chicken to pan until lightly glazed, about 2 minutes.
Cook egg noodles according to package.
Layer pasta in bowl, then noodles, cheese, meat, scallions and top with sesame seed!

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook chopped celery 7 minutes in boiling water and drain. Melt butter in skillet with almonds until brown.
Crush crackers very fine.
Mix with almonds and butter.
Mix celery, water chestnuts, soup and mushrooms together.
Put in casserole dish. Don't grease.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over top of mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients together and then add to egg mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares after cool.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil in large saucepan, butter and water.
Add all other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Frost with White Texas Sheet Cake Frosting (recipe follows).

title: meatball cabbage soup(makes 4 servings; 214 calories each)
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, garlic and savory.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Combine remaining ingredients (including 1 teaspoon Worcestershire).
Heat to boiling.
Drop in meatballs and cook uncovered for 15 minutes. Skim fat from surface of soup.
Remove from heat.

title: creamy roquefort dressing
directions: Cut cream cheese into six pieces.
Place into food processor with mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Pulse until smooth.
Pour milk through food chute with processor running.
Add crumbled cheese by hand.
Use as salad dressing, baked potato topping or dip for fresh vegetables.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut off three slices from one of the onions and put aside. Chop up remaining onions and fry them.
Put aside a couple of slices of bacon, chop the rest and fry with onions.
Mix all beans in a large casserole dish, add the fried onions and bacon and mix together.
Top with the onion and bacon slices you had put aside. Bake in a 400° oven until onions and bacon on top are cooked. This recipe should easily serve 10 people.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Season chicken and brown in a little grease (just enough to cover bottom of pot).
After chicken is brown, take out and brown sausage.
Take out sausage after browning and add onions and bell peppers.
Saute onions and bell peppers on a low fire.
Add meat back in pot.
Add your rice, water, Kitchen Bouquet and salt. Stir.
Cover and cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is done.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
When mixed well, shape into small balls.
Pan-fry on medium heat or bake in oven at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Beat the chicken breasts until very thin.
Marinate chicken in the zesty Italian dressing for 1 hour, turning occasionally.
In large skillet, add enough oil to fry chicken.
To the oil, add butter.
Dip chicken in flour and place in skillet.
Sprinkle with the dry Italian dressing.
Fry until golden brown.

title: swiss beans
directions: Cook beans per directions and drain.
Melt margarine, stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook on low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Fold in green beans and turn into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top and place under broiler for 5 minutes until cheese melts and puffs.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: on the double dinner rolls(yields 24 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, Egg Beaters, Butter Buds and 1 cup of the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in the rest of the flour; continue stirring until smooth.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until it doubles in size (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Spoon batter into 24 muffin cups sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Fill each cup about half full.
Let rise until dough reaches the top of muffin tins (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Separate broccoli and peel stems.
Steam on top of stove over boiling water until barely tender-crisp (or in microwave according to manufacturer's directions).
Put broccoli into sprayed baking dish.
Mix egg, milk and spices and pour over broccoli.
Dot with margarine or sprinkle with oil and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or 6 minutes in microwave.
I use frozen broccoli for convenience.
This is very good, especially with a grain or pasta.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add molasses, egg and applesauce.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in greased 8-inch tube pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: chinese shrimp toast
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Combine shrimp, Five Spices, ginger, egg and cornstarch in blender and puree.
Spoon mixture onto bread and smooth out until it is 1/4-inch thick.
Heat pan of oil about 1/2-inch to 350°.
Put bread in, shrimp side down, until done, about 2 minutes.
Cut bread corner to corner.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Topping:
Have cream cheese at room temperature, softened.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream well.
Spread on jello and sprinkle with nuts which have been chopped extremely fine.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs in frying pan until tender, but not brown.
Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter caramel candy
directions: Boil sugars, syrup and milk together to firm ball stage.
Take from stove, add butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
Add peanut butter and beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered plate or pan.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over oatmeal and butter. Let stand 30 minutes. Soak yeast in 1/3 cup warm water. Add salt, honey, sunflower seeds and yeast to oats mixture. Add flour to make dough kneadable. Knead 10 minutes. Let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down. Divide into 2 loaves. Let rise until double. Mix a few drops of cold water with egg yolk and coat tops of loaves. Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Use 2 (8-inch) pans.

title: marge means bread
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and gradually add flour until dough pulls away from sides.
Mix with dough hook about 10 minutes.
Let dough "rest" in bowl about 20 minutes.
Grease pans and hands and divide dough in equal portions.
Shape into smooth loaves and let rise in pans until double in size.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until brown.
Brush top with butter.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix rest of ingredients and pour in glass pan.
Batter will be thick; you'll have to spread it out.
Bake at 350°.

title: picante sauce
directions: Let simmer until it cooks down and begins to thicken.
Then I use cornstarch to finish thickening to a desired consistency.

title: spinach madeline*
directions: Prepare spinach.
Drain and save liquid.
Melt butter over heat in saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Slowly add liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Mix until melted.
Blend with cooked spinach.
Place in casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Even better next day. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, broth and water in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: tangy cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers in a strainer; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and toss.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse and drain well. Place in a large bowl; add tomatoes and onion.
In a small bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat egg.
Add buttermilk (mix dry ingredients).
Add and mix well.
Add boiling water and mixture together.
Put into hot dish and bake at 500° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped pork chop casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Rub skillet with fat.
Brown chops on both sides, then sprinkle with salt.
In 3 to 4-quart pan, heat water to boil; add carrots and beans and return to boil.
Stir in butter, potatoes and sauce mix. In bowl, mix soup, milk, basil and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for additional 10 to 15 minutes until pork chops are done.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with rolls or biscuits.

title: cheese straws
directions: *For milder taste, use 1 teaspoon ground red pepper.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon 1 teaspoon filling into each pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes. Makes 2 dozen tarts.

title: black bottoms
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well and add 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Beat the next 8 ingredients together; this is the bottom layer.
Line tassie pans with liners. Fill 1/3 full of bottom layer batter and add 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
(Best at about 18 minutes.)
Makes about 65 to 75.

title: german spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain water.
Crush tomatoes with hands and add to spaghetti, then add shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: honey-lemon dressing
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the egg, lemon juice and honey. Cook over low heat while stirring until sauce thickens.
Blend in salt and pepper. Add in sour cream and mix well.
Chill for at least 40 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs. Mix flour and soda together in bowl. Add flour, soda and buttermilk to first ingredients. Add vanilla and bananas. Bake in slow oven at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: special k entree
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with seasonings and eggs.
Add nuts; mix.
Add cereal.
(Mixture will be fairly dry.) Press into cake pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes a 350°.

title: hanky panks
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Return to skillet and add the rest of the ingredients, except bread.
Mix and cook until cheese melts. Spread some mix on each bread slice.
Place on cookie sheet; put under broiler until brown and bubbly.

title: cheesy corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 375°.
Cut in squares and serve hot.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix 7-Up and pineapple juice that have already been in the refrigerator and are cold. Ten or 15 minutes before serving, add sherbet.

title: too easy chicken dinner
directions: Put chicken, soup and onion into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours, then break chicken into smaller pieces (it will be very tender).
Add gravy, peas and mushrooms; cook until heated through.
Serve over noodles, rice or toast.

title: tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter over moderate heat. Add onion and garlic and saute for 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in the tomatoes and their juices, the stock, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil then lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. In a food processor or blender, puree the soup for 1 minute or until smooth. Return the soup to the saucepan and stir in the cream. Heat over moderately low heat for about 5 minutes or just until heated through. Do not boil.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Press seams together. Bake 10 minutes at 425° or until brown (cool).
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Layer vegetables over crust.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: honey popcorn mix
directions: Mix the butter in a medium saucepan over low heat. Add the honey, brown sugar and salt. Cook the mixture, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add baking soda and mix well.

title: creamy dessert
directions: Drain juice from fruits and mix pudding with a little of the juice.
Add fruits and mix well.
Add 1 carton thawed Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add potatoes.
Brown ground beef; drain and put on top of potatoes.
Add green beans on top of hamburger.
Cover with bag of Tater Tots until entire top is covered.
Mix evaporated milk and mushroom soup and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes until heated thoroughly.
Complete meal.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil, add chicken broth and broccoli; cook 5 minutes. Add noodles, cook 4 minutes. Stir in milk and cheese until melted.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, flours and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pink angel cloud
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice strawberries.
Make strawberry jello as per directions, but don't refrigerate until you have added strawberries and Dream Whip, mixed and poured it over cake pieces; then refrigerate it.
Jello will saturate cake; strawberries will settle in among cake pieces.

title: chicken or tuna pot pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on low heat.
Bake one pie crust.
Then pour filling into pie crust.
Cover with other pie crust and bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Make holes in crust prior to baking.

title: pasta with marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine fresh and sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Marinate at room temperature for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil pasta in salted water until al dente, 7 to 10 minutes; drain well and while still hot, toss with tomato mixture.
Coarsely chop basil and combine with pasta. Serve immediately or at room temperature.

title: southern soft-shell tacos
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Heat chili according to directions.
Fill tortillas with equal amounts of rice, chili, salsa and cheese.
Fold over sides of tortilla. Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: different congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water, marshmallows, pineapple (drained, save juice) and bananas.
Let jell.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, butter and egg.
Cook over low heat until thick, then add cream cheese, then chill. After it is chilled add whipped topping.
Spread over top of Jell-O mixture.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add Ro-Tel and chili (mash the beans before adding to cheese).
Mix well.
Serve.

title: fourth of july firecrackers
directions: Place two rounded tablespoons potato salad in center of each ham slice.
Roll up, secure with toothpicks.
Stick a small sprig of parsley in one end for a fuse.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover with cold water in the morning.
Do not drain.
Slowly cook until done.
Pour in baking pan one layer of beans and three slices of bacon and sugar (brown or white to your own decision and taste) until your pan has reached fullness of desire.
Last layer, put bacon on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monterey jack quiche squares
directions: Beat eggs at room temperature with electric beater for 3 minutes, or until thick.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to eggs; beat until smooth.
Stir in cheese and green chilies. Pour mixture into 9-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash.
Boil in salt water until soft.
Drain well and mash.
Mix crushed crackers, small finely chopped onion, milk, salt and pepper.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Put dots of butter on top.
Sprinkle on buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: 24-hour dessert
directions: Crush wafers; put 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Fold pineapple into whipped cream and spread over mixture in pan.
Top with other 1/2 of crumbs.
Chill for at least 24 hours.
Cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream and a cherry, if desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix soda and vanilla with sour cream.
Add alternately with the flour to the butter mixture. Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to a rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.
Yield:
about 16 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over bottom of dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix mushroom soup with 2 cans of water and pour over.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and allow to brown the last 10 or 15 minutes.

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Saute onions in water and oil in skillet.
Add tofu and mash down with fork until all scrambled.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat until flavors are blended.
Tasty hot or cold as a sandwich filler.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Place tamales in bottom of large casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of onions, corn chips and cheese.
Pour beans and chili over this. Repeat layers of 1/3 onion, corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese melts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef with onions in a medium size soup pot. Drain off the excess fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes before serving.

title: raspberry liqueur
directions: Crush raspberries in a gallon jar.
Add sugar; stir well. Add vodka and stir again.
Cover jar loosely and let stand for 21 days; stir occasionally.
Strain and sip; it will make your lips numb!

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm.

title: chicken, pork and shrimp en adobo
directions: Place chicken and pork cubes in a non-metal bowl.
Add vinegar, garlic, bay leaves and salt.
Let stand 10 minutes. Transfer to wok.
Pour in enough chicken broth to cover meat. Cover and simmer until all liquid has evaporated.
Add butter. When melted, add shrimp and wine.
Stir-fry until shrimp are firm and pink.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in 2 greased and well floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin.
Blend in egg and milk.
Bake in a 375° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon juice and butter. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until set in center.
Cool.

title: senator's salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Combine vegetables and stir in vinegar mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275 degrees.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil, and two packages of pudding and mix well according to cake package instructions.
Pour batter into a non-stick or greased cake pan and bake 10 minutes at 275 degrees, another 10 minutes at 300 then 35 minutes at 325.
The cake will be done when a knife, pushed into the center, comes out clean.
For topping, gradually add 1 pkg. of pistachio pudding to a 10 oz container of cool whip, spread on the cooled cake, and refrigerate.

title: joe's scrambled eggs
directions: Mix four ingredients together in bowl.
In skillet, melt 1 teaspoon butter on low heat.
Pour in mixture and cook until done.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add spaghetti sauce and water to beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients excluding noodles in a bowl.
Pour 1 cup of sauce mix in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce mix.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mix over sauce, then noodles, sauce and cheese mix again.
Top with noodles and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil and bake 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: party pizza dough
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk and shortening to flour mixture. Add yeast and water and knead until dough is slightly sticky.
Let rise 1 hour and spread into 2 (9 x 12-inch) cookie pans.
Cover dough with sauce and whatever ingredients you want.
Let rise in pan 15 minutes.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: kugeli
directions: Drain potatoes after grated; add onions, beaten eggs, milk with oleo and salt.
Add bacon.
Mix and pour into greased 8 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
Set aside to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Put margarine in 2-quart oblong casserole and set in 350° oven until melted.

title: beefy tostados
directions: In a bowl mix together roast beef spread, jalapeno relish and chili powder.
Spread on tostado shells.
Top each with tomato, lettuce and onion.
Makes 4 tostados.

title: hot artichoke chili dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extracts and food coloring and beat.
Combine flour and cocoa; add alternately with milk to mixture.
Fold in soda mixed in vinegar. Bake in three 8 or 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls made easy
directions: Thaw bread, but do not let rise.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear one loaf into pieces; drop in pan.
Melt butter, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over torn up loaf.
Tear second loaf; put on top.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Place in a 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Turn out onto waxed paper.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until it resembles crumbs. Reserve 1 cup of crumbly mixture. Spread remaining mixture in long pan, pressing down firmly. Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned. Cool. Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and egg until light and smooth. Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Bake 15 minutes.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, creaming well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, lemon extract, juice and rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 70 to 80 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes; remove from pan.
Makes 1 cake.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain off fat.
In a large mixing bowl, mix other ingredients.
Then add sausage.
Pour into buttered casserole dish (covered) and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.

title: soft buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well about 3 to 4 minutes.
Chill batter in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drop cookies by spoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on each cookie before you bake them. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stirred rice pudding
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, bring milk to a boil; stir in uncooked rice and raisins. Cover.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 40 minutes or until most of the milk is absorbed.
Mixture may appear curdled.
Stir in sugar and vanilla. Spoon into dishes and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in pineapple (with the juice), oil, eggs and carrots.
Beat until blended.
Spray a 10-inch tube pan with a nonstick cooking spray.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (test in the center for doneness).
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then take the cake out of the pan to cool completely.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours.

title: holiday scramble
directions: Mix salad oil and Worcestershire sauce together and pour over mix while stirring.
Sprinkle salts over again while stirring. Mix in roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.
Store in airtight containers.
I use clean large garbage bag to mix ingredients.
Easier than stirring.

title: barbecue sauce(for chicken or spareribs)
directions: Mix ingredients together and set aside.

title: bacon and chicken wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in a baking dish and bake for 20 minutes.
Pour in mushroom soup and cook 40 minutes longer.
Add 1/4 cup water if soup is too thick.

title: pasta-a-la-leftovers
directions: In heavy pan, sprayed with cooking spray, saute onion, carrot and celery until tender.
Add sun-dried tomatoes, leftover meat, vegetables and garlic.
Continue to saute until leftovers are warm.
Add leftover pasta to pan; salt and pepper to taste and heat through.
(A little extra pepper really makes this taste better.)
Transfer servings to warm plates and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese fondue
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk. Stir until thickened.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until melted. Serve with apple slices, veggies and bread sticks.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and honey and add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Alternate sifted dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Dough is quite stiff; add nuts and candied fruit.
Roll and cut.
I usually refrigerate dough overnight for easier handling.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May decorate if desired.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Stir in all other ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Place in shallow baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need 1 grocery bag (paper).

title: nancy's red chicken
directions: Stir sauce ingredients together.
Spread chicken parts in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: "smashed" butternut squash
directions: Peel all veggies. Boil carrots and squash, when soft put in mixer with rest of ingredients. Proceed to blend and "SMASH" together until smooth.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add lettuce, onion and cheese.
Toss together.
Break up Tostitos and toss before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In bottom of Pyrex dish, layer crumbled Ritz crackers.
Mix soup, broth and sour cream together.
Add cut up chicken; stir. Pour on top of crumbled crackers.
Top this mixture with additional crumbled crackers and drizzle melted oleo over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with poppy seed if desired.
Bake at 350° to 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let Velveeta cheese and cream cheese sit at room temperature for a while.
Cream cheese together and add rest of ingredients. Roll in paprika.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix all together; do not drain (all liquids go in).

title: decorator frosting
directions: Put flavoring in water, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Be sure to scrape the bowl while beating.
Any leftover frosting may be kept until needed in the refrigerator.

title: jello cream cheese dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm, then spread topping. For toping, soften cream cheese and whip together with sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts and pour over congealed dessert.

title: tex-mex tofu scramble
directions: Saute mushrooms, green onions, minced onions, dill and pepper. Rinse tofu, cut into small cube and place on paper towels to absorb water.
When tofu is drained, add to onions and mushrooms. Stir.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Serve on a tortilla.
Grate cheese over it; add salsa.
Yum!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook the first three ingredients in lightly salted water until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Slowly add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add cheese; blend until melted.
Preheat oven to 325°. Layer the drained cabbage mixture and cheese sauce in a greased casserole.
Make several layers ending with sauce.
Bake until bubbly.
Top with crumbs.
Return to oven until lightly browned.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients in separate bowl.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Put butter and oil in a large skillet over high heat.
Butter will foam.
When foam subsides, butter is hot enough.
Add mushrooms (they should be dry).
Toss them and shake the pan or keep them moving with a spatula until lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, seasoned salt and pepper.
Stir.
Serve with steak or mix with peas.
Makes 2 to 3 servings with steak or 4 servings with 1 package frozen peas.

title: cucumber and yogurt dip
directions: Scrub cucumber to remove wax.
Grate the unpeeled cucumber and drain very well until almost dry.
(Drain yogurt in cheesecloth.) Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
Yield: 1 3/4 cups. One-half cup equals 45 calories, 1 tablespoon equals 5 calories.

title: "no work" brisket of beef
directions: Place brisket in lined foil roasting pan.
Use enough foil to seal and cover.
Place seasonings on top of meat.
Add enough water to make sauce for meat.
Seal tightly and bake at 200° to 250° until meat is capable of shredding or done to own taste.
Great for French roll sandwiches or serve with mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: low-fat potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

Mix "butter" granules according to package directions. Cut each potato in half. Scoop out the center, leaving about 1/4-inch of potato on the inside. Cut skins into quarters. Dab the liquid butter onto the white side of each piece. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake, skin side down, on a baking sheet 5 minutes more.
Serve with fat-free sour cream and salsa.

title: velvet salad
directions: Put pineapple (juice and all) and Jell-O into a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Immediately remove from heat.
When pineapple-Jell-O mixture is completely cool, add other 3 ingredients.
Mix and enjoy!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Butter inside of double boiler. Steam 45 minutes or bake in oven at 325° for same amount of time. This can be served with a white sauce, to which a small can of green peas have been added.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover broccoli with chicken chunks.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together and spread over chicken layer.
Cover with Stove Top stuffing mixture and bake (uncovered) at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Stir flour, baking powder and sugar in a large bowl. Cut in shortening evenly. Stir in milk with a fork. Stir in cheese. Place butter and garlic in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven until butter melts. Remove pan from oven; stir in parsley. Form small dough balls about 1/4 cup size. Drop into melted butter; turn to coat well. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until just golden. Spoon any remaining butter on top. Serve warm. Makes 12.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin and other ingredients, except the cake mix, as for pie.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine, drizzle over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cape cod cranberry pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Spread the cranberries in the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the sugar and nuts.
Add the remaining sugar to the eggs, beating well.
Beat in the flour, butter and shortening.
Pour over cranberries.
Bake for about 1 hour, or until crust is golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cote boeuf chalonnaise(french; from la provence)
directions: Saute steaks in oiled skillet for 3 to 4 minutes on each side on medium fire for medium rare steaks.
Remove steaks when desired doneness is reached.
Set aside and keep warm.
Add to same skillet the tablespoon of shallots or onion, garlic, thyme, chopped parsley and dry red wine.
Add 4 ounces of butter and when butter has melted, swish the butter and sauce together gently.
Pour over steaks when hot and serve.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While warm, take pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil.
Punch holes in cake and pour over cake.
Mix pudding and pour over cake.
Let cake cool.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with a few crushed potato chips.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine eggs, salt and milk. Add flour or enough to make a stiff dough. Roll thin on floured surface. Let stand a half hour. Cut into strips and let dry 2 hours or so. Add to chicken broth or soup of your choice.

title: new england chicken stew
directions: Cover chicken with water and boil until done.
Take chicken out of broth to cool.
While chicken is cooking, peel and cut up vegetables.
Cook vegetables in broth until tender.
Cut chicken up and put in vegetables.
(If you want this to be low-fat, take skin and fat off chicken before you cook it and add 2 chicken bouillon cubes.)
When vegetables are almost done, mix 1 1/2 cups cold water with cornstarch and sugar.
Add to mixture and stir gently.
Season to taste.
Enjoy.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box. Pour over coconut and pecans in pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls on cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with 1 tablespoon of melted butter.
Beat egg and water with a fork in a shallow dish.
Mix flour and salt in another shallow dish.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Mix lettuce, hamburger, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Just before serving, add dressing and chips.

title: cinnamon sugar triangles
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
On ungreased cookie sheet unroll dough.
Brush top with butter. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cut through dough along original lines.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with snack crackers or vegetables.

title: herbed flounder
directions: Arrange frozen fillets on foil covered rack of broiler pan. Mix margarine, onion, sage and thyme.
Spread over fillets.
Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Broil with tops 3 to 4 inches from heat, brushing occasionally with margarine, until fillets flake easily with fork 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Cut chicken breasts into chunks.
In 10-inch skillet over high heat, cook chicken and salt in hot oil until tender.
Remove chicken.
In drippings, cook onion until tender.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in chicken, pinto beans, Ro-Tel, and sugar.
Heat through.
Warm tortillas.
Top each tortilla with about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in lengthwise strip down center. Fold left and right sides of each tortilla over mixture, fold one end under.
Top with tomatoes, guacamole, or salsa.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half of mixture in casserole dish, then put 1/2 of cheese on top.
Pour remaining mixture on top; sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until real hot.
The Ro-Tel with chilies can be chopped in blender.

title: 14-carat cake*
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, salad oil and eggs; mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut; blend thoroughly.

title: chocolate layered cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on pkg.
Bake in 2 9-inch round pans, cool.
Whip pudding and set aside.
In a large, high, round container, place on one layer of cake and break it up with a fork. Pour 1\2 of the pudding over cake.
Add one container of cool whip. Repeat layer.
For extra flavor add 3 crushed Heath Bars to each layer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In heavy skillet or large electric skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Add onion, pepper and spices, etc.
(except rice).
Stir and cook 15 minutes.
Add rice, salt and consomme or water.
Bring quickly to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until done (about 15 minutes), then add peas and pimento.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add extracts and beat.
Add flour, cocoa and milk alternately.
Add soda mixed in vinegar.
Bake in three 1 layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage and eggs casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain well.
Place sausage in 9-inch casserole.
Place bread crumbs on next, then the grated cheese.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy and pour over entire mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Needs no seasoning.
Serve with coffee cake and fruit.
This is easy and has become a holiday tradition for our family.
This is super for New Year's Eve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until dumplings are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: vietnamese salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Add sliced onion and stir until onion is not hot.
Taste the mixture often to make sure it is not too sweet or too sour.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour (mixed with salt, pepper and paprika).
Brown in shortening.
Remove chicken pieces.
Add 1 tablespoon paprika and onion.
Add mushroom soup to shortening in skillet.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer one hour. Remove chicken and slowly stir in sour cream.
Serve over chicken and cooked noodles.

title: banana-blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Stir in banana.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Add blueberry mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir until just moist.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix together and make soft dough.
Knead quickly and roll to desired thickness.
Cut and put on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside. Place half of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half of the beans.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer bacon and vegetables.
In a second bowl, combine sugar, cheese and dressing.
Just before serving, pour dressing over and stir.
Top with croutons.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Place 2 kinds of chocolate chips and almond bark in a cake pan.
Bake at 200° for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix together.
Add peanuts and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: cocktail crackers
directions: Mix all together and pour over crackers.
Let set for 1/2 hour.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: tasty dry chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except butter.
Slowly melt butter in pan and add marinated chicken.
Braise until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: "my mother's" salad dressing
directions: Add sugar, paprika and salt to mixture of catsup, vinegar, onion, oil, lemon juice and garlic or Blue cheese; beat in blender or processor.

title: puerto rican rice and beans
directions: In 6-quart stew pot with cover, wash and strain rice 3 times. Set aside.
Take first 11 ingredients and place in pot over medium/high flame and stir for approximately 5 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and broil until bacon is crispy.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar and some Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Put in crock-pot and simmer for 2 hours.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Stir in pineapple juice. Heat on low until thickens.
Mix small portion of thickened mixture with beaten egg yolk.
Add to saucepan and cook a minute or two.
Take off heat and stir in pineapple.
Delicious between yellow cake layers.

title: patsy's hot bacon dressing for spinach salad
directions: Toss and serve with the dressing (recipe follows).

title: malted milk pie
directions: Mix 1 c. crushed malted milk ball with frozen yogurt and spread into graham cracker crust.
Mix cool whip with remaining 1/2 c. crushed malted milk balls.
Spread over frozen yogurt mixture.
Freeze and serve.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion and bell pepper in water in saucepan over low heat until tender; drain.
Combine with corn bread and bread crumbs in bowl.
Add eggs, butter, sage, salt and enough broth to make moist consistency.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until heated through, but not dry.
Yield: 10 servings or more.

title: quesadilla
directions: Amounts will vary as to the number prepared.

title: apple-acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and scape out seed.
Place cut side down in baking dish and bake for 25 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Turn squash cut side up and fill with apple mixture.
Continue baking for 20 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: macaroni saute
directions: Saute macaroni, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until macaroni is slightly yellow. Add tomato juice and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and put in casserole or heavy bowl.
Fry bacon.
Remove and pat grease dry.
Fry onions in bacon grease until tender, but not brown.
Mix sugar and mustard together.
Add to onions in frypan.
Add beaten eggs and vinegar to onion mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon and egg slices and mix. Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: twin mountain blueberry cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Combine eggs and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15-20 minutes.
Makes 32-34 cookies.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: baked scrambled eggs
directions: Heat oven to 250 degrees, grease large 9x12 pan.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator 24 hours, stirring at intervals.
Put in freezer containers.
Seal and freeze.

title: sweet chicken delight
directions: In large bowl, combine soup mix, apricot preserves and Catalina dressing.
Add chicken to this mixture and marinate 8 hours in refrigerator.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish with butter.
Blend soup and milk; arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and soup.
Sprinkle each layer with a little black pepper.
Sprinkle cheese on top; dot with margarine.
Sprinkle sparingly with paprika.
Cover with foil; bake 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake another 15 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: picnic lemon bars
directions: Cream 1/4
cup	10x
sugar
and
butter until light and fluffy.
Add
cup
flour
and
salt;
mix well.	Press into lightly greased
9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Combine
eggs, sugar, soda, lemon rind and juice and 2 teaspoons flour.
Beat well; pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Cool; cut into bars. Makes 16 bars.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll into balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Pour chocolate over balls.

title: olympic cookies
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; add soda and salt and mix until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: quick-n-easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
In a large skillet, cook chicken slowly in teriyaki sauce.
While chicken is cooking, prepared rice as per directions on the box.
Cut green onions and cook in separate pot.
Add carrots and onion and cook until tender.
When chicken is browned and cooked, add finished rice, vegetables and small amount teriyaki sauce.
Mix together and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add scrambled eggs.

title: snow cap casserole
directions: Rehydrate Granburger with hot water for 10 minutes.
Pour a little oil into a Dutch oven.
Saute the Granburger, onion and carrots in oil until onion is tender.
Add soup, mushrooms, beans and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Place mixture in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
