Combine whipped potatoes and remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spread potato mixture over the Granburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease pan and lay boiled cooked chicken in bottom. Mix mushroom and sour cream together and pour over chicken. Break up crackers on top. Cook at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: indiana chocolate cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a brisk boil.
Pour over next 2 ingredients.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Beat by hand.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Cut corn from cobs, scraping cobs to remove all milk.
Measure 2 cups corn and set aside.
Combine egg yolks, milk, cheese, cracker crumbs, butter, salt, pepper and dill weed in a large bowl; add corn and stir well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar at high speed of an electric mixer until soft peaks form; fold whites into corn mixture.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine the Oreos and butter; press firmly in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt 1 cup of the chocolate chips, the condensed milk and the vanilla.
Stir frequently to prevent the bottom from burning.
Pour over the Oreo crust and top with the nuts and 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until it sets.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: tuxedo chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in glass baking dish. Season however you wish; seasonings listed are merely a suggestion.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour, uncovered. Make dressing per instructions on package and put over top of chicken.
Cover dish with foil and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Mix rest of ingredients in pan, bring to a boil over low heat and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in soft gelatin.
Chill until partly set.
Beat until smooth.
Carefully fold in meringue of 3 eggs, 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 6 tablespoons sugar; pile into cooked crust. Chill until set, 2 hours.
Garnish with whipping cream.

title: chiffon birthday cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Place flour, baking powder, water, oil, sugar, extract and egg yolks into a separate bowl and
beat.
Fold
in	egg whites and pour into an ungreased 14 inch
round
pan
or
oblong pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Decorate to your satisfaction.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix in order; add oats last.
Stir until mixed.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; frost with chocolate frosting and cut in bars.

title: little cheddar loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients, except last 3.
Shape into 6 small loaves.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over top of loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 loaves.

title: tangy orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add frozen juice.
Stir well to dissolve.
Add drained mandarin oranges and pineapple (including juice).

title: zucchini soup
directions: Put into large soup pot.
Cook until everything is soft. Puree in blender.
Put back into soup pot.
Add 1 can evaporated milk.

title: punch
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and tea bag.
Let set 5 minutes. Squeeze out tea bag and cool.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and ginger ale.
Freeze cherries in ring for punch bowl or in ice cubes for water pitcher.

title: carrie's homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring 3 cups of water to boil; add noodles.
Cook until done. Pour off water.
Add butter and milk, cooking over low heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a square pan and add ingredients by layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and ground nutmeg, stirring well.
Set mixture aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened. (Dough will be soft.)
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface and knead 4 to 5 times, adding more flour as needed.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
10 biscuits.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add one slightly beaten egg to dry mixture.
Put apple mixture in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle over apples; drizzle melted margarine and cinnamon over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: white taffy
directions: Combine sugar, 1/3 cup water and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring to light crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat; add vinegar and baking soda and mix thoroughly.
Pour on buttered platter to cool.
Butter hands, then pull taffy until it is snow white and porous.
When candy is too hard to pull, twist into a rope of desired thickness.
Cool and break into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Yield:
2 dozen pieces of candy.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients; beat well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mushroom chicken on rice
directions: Put all ingredients into pot and cook until celery and onions are cooked.
Put over hot cooked rice.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients as listed, mixing after each addition.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray and floured.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; then lower heat to 300° and bake 55 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and let cool for about 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: clam cheese dip
directions: Drain clams and save liquid.
Soften cream cheese 20 to 30 seconds on medium in a 1-quart (1 liter) microproof casserole. Mix cream cheese, onion, lemon juice and clam liquid well.
Add salt to taste.
If mixture is too thick, add more clam liquid for easy dunking.
Serve fresh vegetables or crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: miss blanche's cookies
directions: Press into pan in layers.
Spread over top of layers Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: szechuan stir-fry
directions: Place flank steak in the freezer for 10 minutes.

title: syrup pies
directions: Mix well and pour into uncooked pie shells.
Cook until set. (This recipe makes two pies.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash and onions until tender; drain.
Put half in a greased baking dish; add salt and pepper, 1/2 can soup and 4 slices of cheese.
Then add remaining squash.
Add other 1/2 can of soup, cheese and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: mary todd lincoln's white almond cake
directions: Grate by hand or in a blender enough almonds to total one cup. Do not pack in the measure.
Sift the flour with the baking powder and set aside.
Cream the butter until very light, then add 1 3/4 cups of sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add the sifted ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Fold in the almonds, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat the egg whites with the salt and remaining 1/4 cup sugar to soft peaks, then fold gently but thoroughly into the batter.
Pour into a well buttered and floured 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake begins to pull from sides of the pan.
Cool cake upright in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Then loosen around edges and turn out on a rack.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: award winning peaches and cream pie(this has an unusual crust.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease sides and bottom of a 10 inch deep-dish pie pan.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and pudding mix.
Mix in butter, egg, and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes now pour this mixture into pie pan.
Arrange sliced peach slices on top of pudding mixture.
In a small mixing bowl, beast cream cheese until fluffy, add 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoon reserve peach syrup, beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon mixture over peaches to within 1 inch of pan edge.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, and sprinkle over top.
Use Freestone Peaches in heavy syrup.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Chill and serve.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat the daylights out of them! Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350 degrees for about ten minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in water; drain.
In saucepan, saute onion in butter, then add cheese and stir until melted.
Then add soup. Put 3/4 cup dressing in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add cabbage and cover with cheese, onion and soup mix.
Cover with remaining 1/2 cup dressing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. or until it is hot all through it.

title: orange jello-mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Cool slightly, then add pineapple with juice, the drained Mandarin oranges and the sour cream.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
(If you like a sweeter taste, cut down sour cream to 1/2 to 3/4 cup.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes (do not peel).
Cover with water and boil about 25 minutes, until tender.
Peel, cut in half and slice thin. Brown bacon in pan.
Remove bacon.
Saute onion in bacon fat until soft, not brown.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add vinegar, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Remove from heat and add mustard, pour mixture over potatoes, add bacon.
Serve warm.
May be reheated.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Sift flour; rub in shortening with knife or fingertips.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Drop a tablespoon at a time into chicken broth the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking time.
The pan must be covered closely.
The cover must not be removed during cooking.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Add washed chicken wings.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours, overnight.
Turn bag every 4 hours.
Place wings on a foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; turn to brown opposite side after 1/2 hour.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs; add sour cream.
Stir in raisins, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Place this in a 9-inch pie shell.
Place top crust over filling.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes or more until filling is set.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
(Try baking without top crust.)

title: chili beans
directions: Mix pinto beans, kidney beans, cuminos, red chili powder, sugar, salt and pepper in a large pot.
Add 2 cups of water and let simmer for 20 minutes.
While beans are simmering, brown ground beef with chopped bell pepper, salt and pepper; drain fat. Stir in ground beef, tomato paste and whole tomatoes in with pot of beans.
Add 1 cup of water.
Stir and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally and add more water if needed.
(You decide how thick you want the chili to be.)
Grate cheese and chop onions for toppings.

title: daddy's delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O in mixing bowl. Drain all fruit, then add to mixture.
Stir well and fold in serving dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Combine oil and butter in a 3-quart pot.
Cook slowly for 1/2 hour; the mixture will turn a deep brown color.
Set aside after cooking.
Add water and broth in large pot and bring to a boil. Cook chicken for 1/2 hour; skim off excess fat.
Remove chicken from pot.
When cool, skin, bone and dice chicken.
Discard skin and bones.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat 1/2 cup butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each is added. Add flour and baking soda; alternate with buttermilk.
Add in candy mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: crazy apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and egg; beat until smooth.
Add milk; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to mixture; beat until smooth. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay apple slices on top. Sprinkle with sugar mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove; sprinkle top with heavy cream and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: praline cake
directions: Make regular cake batter or cake mix and cook in sheet pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pauline's tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic in pot. Add all other ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes.
Yields about 9 (1 cup) servings.
Exchanges:
2 meat exchanges, 3/4 bread exchange and 1/2 fat exchange.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Put crushed crackers in.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Chop dates and add pecans.
Add to mix, then pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: beef sukiyaki
directions: Brown meat in Teflon pan or Wok with 1/4 c. water.
Add more water if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients except spinach and bean sprouts.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Add spinach and bean sprouts.
Mix again.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve immediately over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: party o's
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Combine cereal, pretzel sticks and nuts in ungreased pan.
Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, paprika and garlic salt.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Toss until coated. Bake 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 7 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of margarine; stir in the sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk.
Bring these ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Set on a cooling rack; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Stir well to mix.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs in 1/2 cup melted oleo and press into a shallow 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup oleo until clear.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle cheese over onions.
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings well and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it is set like a custard.
Cool before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix Velveeta, Rotel and beef together. Cook on stove top or in microwave until all is blended together. Serve warm.

title: shrimp with feta cheese(garides me feta)
directions: Pour lemon juice over shrimp and let stand.
In a heavy frying pan, heat oil.
Add onions (green and white) and garlic; saute until limp.
Add tomato puree and wine; simmer 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Blend cheese with milk.
Add eggs, lemon juice, salt and nutmeg, then add parsley and broccoli.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: jogging juice in a jug
directions: Mix well and chill.
Drink small glassfull morning and night.

title: pork chops and brown rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put rice in bottom of baking dish.
Place chops on top of rice and onion and pepper slices on chops.
Mix water and consomme; pour over all.
Bake covered about 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 350°.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix 3 ingredients together, drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes great little nugget.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Wash and slice squash. Beat egg in medium bowl and add water, salt and pepper, stir.
Add enough flour to make a sticky batter, mixing well.
Add squash or stir to coat each piece. Fry in oil until golden brown and crispy. Serves 4 persons.

title: buffet bread
directions: Remove crust from bread; slice diagonally, not quite all the way through, in 1-inch slices.
Combine margarine, thyme and salad dressing mix.
Spread mixture between slices and over top and sides of loaf.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: farmer's flapjacks
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a mixing bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, add egg, flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and butter, mixing thoroughly.
Fry on a preheated greased griddle.
Makes 1 dozen. Good with fried apples and sausage or bacon.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm. Put cherry pie filling on cake.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Saute bacon and put aside.
Saute ham pieces. Add bacon, onions, cooked limas, corn and tomato sauce. Cover with a lid and cook in oven or on top of stove on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Separate rolls and place in 9 x 12 casserole dish.
Place sausage on crust, then potatoes, then top with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over sausage, potatoes and cheese.	Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco beef salad
directions: Season beef strips with salt.
Add cherry tomatoes, avocado, green pepper and onion.
Mix
chili sauce, oil, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and garlic.
Add meat and vegetables and toss.
Serve individual portions on bed of lettuce.
Serve corn chips and grated cheese to sprinkle on top.
Makes four to five servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add cranberry juice.
Let set.
Spread sour cream over this when jelled.

title: date creole roll
directions: Cook milk and sugar over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until soft ball stage is reached. Add dates.
Cook two or three minutes more.
Remove from heat. Cool until lukewarm.
Add nuts.
Stir until real thick.
Turn out on a piece of wet cloth and roll to form roll.
Place in refrigerator.
Slice to serve.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine all but chicken in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Put chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over.
Cover and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix kraut and sugar together; let stand 2 hours. Combine other ingredients with kraut mixture. Cover tightly and chill for 2 hours or longer. Will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: corn souffle
directions: Scrub Idaho potatoes, one for each serving.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Spread each potato with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise and sprinkle with Mrs. Dash seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: sweet milk doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Beat in sugar and add melted shortening.
Sift baking powder, salt and nutmeg with 1 cup flour; stir into first mixture.
Alternate flour to make a very soft dough.
Chill.
Roll out on floured board and cut in shape.
Drop in hot lard.

title: three vegetable casserole
directions: Heat soups and milk over low heat.
Drain lima beans, asparagus and green peas; put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup and milk mixture over the vegetables.
Top this with 3/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: diabetic pineapple glazed yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine reserved pineapple juice, mixed with cornstarch, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Combine yams and pineapple in 8-inch round casserole.
Stir in sauce and coat well.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with foil and bake for 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.
Serving size:
1/4 recipe. Exchanges:
1 bread and 1/2 fruit.

title: easter houska
directions: This recipe can be halved, quartered or cut in thirds; however, if full recipe is made, it freezes very well when baked.

title: kentucky transparent pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add salt, milk and vanilla. Place in unbaked shell and bake for 45 minutes.

title: crispy cheese crackers
directions: Mix butter, cheese and flour until well blended.
Add cereal; mix well.
Roll into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: overnight egg dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter the bread; place 8 slices, butter side down in pan.
Place cheese atop.
Place shredded ham atop.
Top with remaining 8 slices of bread, butter side up.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread; refrigerate overnight. Place mushrooms on top.
Mix cornflakes and melted butter.
(Can be mixed in Ziploc bag in advance.)
Place over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 30 minutes before cutting.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix egg yolks, salt and sugar in top of double boiler to blend, add milk.
Cook until spoon coats, do not boil.
Cool, add vanilla and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add orange peel.
Chill over night.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until browned.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans; heat.

title: plum bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add eggs, oil and baby food.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Blend together in processor.
Shape into ball and roll in pecan chips.
Refrigerate.
Better if made the day before using.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: I had to trade my white chocolate cheesecake recipe for this carefully guarded secret.

title: delicious chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and season
with salt and pepper.
Cook in skillet with butter, adding small amounts of water (no more than 1/4 cup) occasionally if necessary.
Add broccoli and cheese packs and let simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: dandy dog mix
directions: Roll wieners in mix and fry in hot shortening.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Stir in milk.
Add peanuts. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat wet ingredients together well, then add to dry ingredients and mix until well moistened. Mixture may be stored up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake in microwave for 2 minutes on High.

title: golden harvest cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients gradually until mixed.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut with a spoon.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy 1 1/2 quart saucepan; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil 4 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add 1 cup Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat remaining ingredients, substitute peanut butter for chocolate.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: home salad stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix
together the ham, celery, pecans, olives and onion in a large
bowl.
Stir
in
the
mayonnaise and chili sauce. Placing the stem down on a board, cut each tomato about 2/3 of the way down into 8 wedges.
Gently push wedges open to allow space
for stuffing.
Place
each
tomato
on a lettuce lined plate
and stuff with ham salad.
Garnish plates with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, dry vanilla pudding, butter, egg and milk in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased glass pie plate.

title: roast turkey legs (wings)
directions: Rub turkey legs (wings) with butter or oil, thyme, salt and pepper.
Roast at 450° for 20 minutes.
Baste twice with mixture of butter and wine.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Cover pan with foil and continue roasting for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until turkey is tender.
During the last 20 minutes, uncover pan, so the turkey will get brown and crisp.

title: sticky buns or pecan rolls
directions: Boil potato; mash potato and add potato water and 1 scant cup sugar; let cool.
Dissolve yeast cakes in lukewarm water; add to potato mixture and let stand in warm place 1 hour.
Heat milk; add shortening.
Cool.
Add 1 scant cup sugar, salt and eggs.
Add to other mixture.
Add flour; let rise until double in size.
Knead and roll out.
Spread with melted butter, cinnamon and raisins. Roll up and cut into 2-inch pieces.

title: maple syrup doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl, combine maple syrup, milk, eggs and shortening; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients, except oil; mix until a soft dough forms.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter into rounds.

title: coconut chewy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar, set aside.
Beat sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla & flavoring till fluffy.
Stir in 1 c. coconut.
Using teaspoon, roll into balls and roll in coconut. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie 1
directions: Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Pour on raw crust and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 1 large loaf pan or 4 mini loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients well; pour in pan and bake 1 hour.
Great when sliced and spread with soft cream cheese!

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt onto wax paper.
Melt margarine in medium-sized saucepan over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars and peanut butter; beat with mixer well.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla until thick and creamy.
Stir in flour mixture with wooden spoon until thoroughly combined.

title: pineapple and coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in two 8-inch pans.
Divide layers into 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and pineapple together.
Pour 1/4 filling on top of each layer and sprinkle frozen coconut on top of each layer as you stack each one. Then, when you stack all four, cover with Cool Whip and finish with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: yeast bread angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to buttermilk; stir well.
Add to flour mixture; mix until blended.
Knead for 1 minute or until smooth. Roll in 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
This dough may be stored in bulk for 3 or 4 days in the refrigerator.
It is also good for cinnamon rolls. Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into large baking dish.
Top with a mixture of 2 cups finely crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Leave covered until about last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until light brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh peach pudding
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Line serving dish with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Pour 1/2 peach mixture over wafers.
Place more wafers over the mixture, then add remaining peach mixture.
Top with more vanilla wafers or peach slices and chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine warm water and yeast; stir until dissolved.
Next, mix remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add water and yeast mixture. Knead a few times.
You may add extra flour if needed.
Pour oil in pan.
Put dough balls in pan.
Turn over to coat with oil.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and butter. Spread over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: health munchies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Makes 30 to 40 balls.
These are healthful as well as tasty.
Keep cool until served.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Mix bread crumbs, oregano, basil, salt and garlic on a large flat dish.
Slice zucchini 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
One at a time, dip into egg and coat with bread crumb mix. Cover bottom of pan with oil.
Fry zucchini a few at a time, turning often, until brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
Thinly slice cheese. Spread some tomato sauce in pan, single layer of zucchini.
Spoon tomato sauce and layer Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, topping with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve.

title: aunt jane's corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into patties. Fry in deep fat.

title: three bean surprise
directions: Drain beans and mix with French dressing.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pineapple lemon delight
directions: Mix together jello and water and cool to room temperature. Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
When jello is cool, add cream cheese mixture to it.
Whip 1 can Milnot that has been chilled overnight.
Fold jello and cream cheese mixture into Milnot and add 1 cup drained crushed pineapple.
Pour over crust and refrigerate.
May sprinkle few graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour one-half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with milk and pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over this, then sprinkle with nuts.
Pour the other half of batter over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Put onion in a small amount of oil.
Brown hamburger when onion has been browned a little.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, Texas Pete and chili powder.
Simmer 45 minutes or longer.
Taste. May want to add seasonings to taste.

title: lenten chocolate cake
directions: Measure into large mixing bowl the flour, baking soda, cocoa, salt and sugar.
Add vinegar, vanilla, oil and cold water.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan which has been oiled or lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Fresh strawberries are also good on top.

title: poppy parmesan straws
directions: Stir cheese with poppy seeds, set 1/2 aside.
On lightly floured waxed paper, roll out 1/2 of the pastry to 12-inch square. Beat egg yolk with water; brush lightly over pastry.
Sprinkle with about 1/3 of cheese mixture.
Roll lightly.
Fold in half crosswise; roll out to 12-inch square.
Brush with egg mixture and sprinkle with cheese mixture and roll out lightly.
Turn pastry over, brush lightly with egg and sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture.
Repeat with reserved pastry and cheese mixture.
With sharp knife, cut each pastry into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Holding each strip by ends, twist into a spiral.
Place 1/2 inch apart on greased baking sheets, pressing down the ends.
Brush ends with egg.
Bake in 425°
oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden and crisp.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over medium heat; stir and mix. Add egg; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Mix marshmallows and nuts in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mix over marshmallows and nuts; mix well.
Divide mix in half.
Sprinkle wax paper with confectioners sugar.
Shape each half into 8-inch roll.
Roll up tight.
Chill several hours.
Slice when cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar and zucchini.
Then add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oven-baked ribs and kraut
directions: Place ribs, meaty side down, in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove meat from oven; drain off excess fat.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Combine sauerkraut, potatoes, broth, pimiento and celery seed.
Place in baking dish. Separate onion into rings; place sauerkraut mixture on top of ribs, meaty side up, in center of dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Brush barbecue sauce over ribs; cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: hot rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl put 2 cups warm water; add rest of ingredients (except yeast and flour).
Dissolve well, add yeast and dissolve.
Add half of flour and stir until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix until real smooth.
Let dough rest 3 to 5 minutes; then put out on floured board and knead as biscuits lightly.
Let dough rest 5 minutes longer and put out into greased muffin pans.
Let rolls rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours and bake in oven 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Brush rolls with butter after done.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease off.
Add all other ingredients.
Brown bun halves and spoon a spoonful on each bun. Place a slice of cheese on top.
Melt under broiler.
Very good.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Pour off excess fat. Combine catsup, sugar and mustard; spread over meat.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed; mix 1/2 of shredded coconut with cake mix.
While cake is warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour 3/4 can of cream of coconut over cake.
Mix remaining cream of coconut and shredded coconut with 8 ounces whipped topping.
Spread on cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: yogurt cheese(good for weight watchers)
directions: Line a strainer with coffee filters for cheesecloth.
Pour the yogurt into the filter and set the strainer within another bowl to catch the whey that will drain from the yogurt.
Let the yogurt stand in the refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Do not throw the whey (liquid) out, use in a recipe that calls for milk.

title: easy breakfast rolls
directions: Butter a large Bundt pan; lay frozen dinner rolls and then layer with other ingredients.
Place a towel over top; let stand overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 1/4 cups sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat egg yolks; add to cornstarch mixture.
Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat and then boil gently 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in cooked and cooled pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread to cover filling well.
Bake in 425° oven for 4 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Makes 9-inch pie. Cool on cake rack.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix laundry starch with cup of cold water to make a smooth paste.
Add 5 cups hot water and place on medium heat.
Stir until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Stir in Ivory flakes.
Divide in portions for coloring.

title: coconut-pecan pie
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into pastry. Bake
for
to 50 minutes or until filling is set. Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: texas party dip
directions: Saute
hamburger meat
until
brown.
Drain
well.
Add onion and cook until
tender.
Add
remaining
ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve in a slow cooker or a fondue dish to keep
hot.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Keep on low heat.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken; cool.
Skim off fat.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute pepper and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to chicken.
Make sauce (3 cups).
Add cooking sherry last.
Pour over chicken, mushrooms and peppers.

title: pizza boats
directions: Brown beef and cook according to directions on taco seasoning mix pack.
Brown buns lightly. Top with pizza sauce, beef mix and cheese.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Stir in both milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture begins to bubble.
Cover.
Cook for 3 minutes without stirring. Uncover and stir gently.
Continue cooking; stir occasionally until candy thermometer registers 236° or until a small amount of candy dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and let cool for 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat candy until creamy and thick.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
When cool and firm, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 36 squares.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Sift together the corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, combine beaten egg, milk and cracklings.
Combine with dry ingredients; beat well.
Pour into a hot, greased pan. Bake in moderate oven until done and brown.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter and marshmallow.

title: copper pennies carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, but not mushy.
Drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan; slowly bring to simmer over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 or 3 weeks.

title: texas crabgrass
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Slowly melt butter; add onion and saute.
Add spinach, crab, cheese and sherry and heat thoroughly. Serve with Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift flour, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Coat raisins with flour.
Add floured raisins, almonds and figs to batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Roll spareribs in flour and brown in butter.
Remove to baking pan.
Melt butter and brown onions.
Add rest of ingredients and, while hot, pour over ribs.
Line pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt butter.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients to flour.
Mix well and knead until dough is soft.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until it's double in size (about 2 hours).
Punch down and rise for 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons mix to 6 ounces hot water.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon flour in cup and level off.
In medium bowl mix dry ingredients, except sugar.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Cool, skin and coarsely grate. Heat margarine with soup; add onion.
Blend in sour cream, lightly stir in cheese.
Add to potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch container.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle corn flakes over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: carol's zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini and all dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour mixture into two oiled and floured loaf pans, 8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes two loaves.
Cool in pans 10 minutes and remove.
Invert loaves onto racks and cool.
Serve warm with butter.

title: picante dip
directions: Pour picante sauce and cream cheese in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut red onions on top of mixture.
Cover with torn lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease and heat a large cast-iron skillet.
Combine corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into hot greased skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Yield: 10 servings.

title: max's spinach dip
directions: Squeeze thawed spinach until well drained; mix well with remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 hours.
Hollow out round bread and reserve bread that was removed for dipping.
Fill bread with dip and serve.

title: baked ziti with veggies
directions: Prepare pasta as label directs; drain.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil.
Cook carrots, broccoli and green pepper 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until veggies are tender, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, toss cooked veggies with pasta, Mozzarella and grated Parmesan cheese.
Spoon into prepared casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water and let stand for 20 minutes. While waiting, cream butter.
Add sugars, beaten eggs, self-rising flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Combine with oatmeal. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly
touched.

title: coconut tea cookies
directions: Cut margarine into sugar and add sifted flour.
Mix with hands to a soft dough and press evenly into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan, pressing a little up side about 1/2-inch.
Prick with fork and bake at 350° until it begins to turn golden (15 minutes).
Drain 1 can pineapple well.
Spread this over crust.
Beat 1 egg well and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until thick and light colored and fold in 1 1/2 cup coconut.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Return to oven and bake until topping browns slightly, about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: heavenly spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Saute beef until brown.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper in mixing bowl. Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Spread half the spaghetti on bottom; cover with all of cheese mixture.
Add remaining spaghetti. Spread tomato meat sauce on top.
Cover; keep in refrigerator until 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with cheese slices, if desired.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Fry hamburger meat and drain.
Add onion and seasoning and stir for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes and let boil.
Add cabbage and let simmer until cabbage is tender, about 30 minutes.
Do not stir after cabbage has been added.

title: frenchies
directions: Grind all together and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Hollow out 30 small French rolls.
Fill liberally.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven until very hot.
This freezes real well and can even be put frozen into the rolls; just freeze leftover amount.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Fill a gallon jug with sliced cucumbers (about 1/4 inch thick).
Add one cup plain salt and water to fill jug.
Soak 4 days.
Wash and soak 24 hours in two tablespoons of alum and water to cover cucumbers.
Wash and cover with vinegar for 10 days. Wash and add 3 cups sugar each day for 3 days.
Add pickling spice in a cloth (however much you like).
May be put in pint jars or left in gallon jug.

title: fish scallop
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients until smooth.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to moderate (350°). Continue baking about 35 minutes or until custard is firm.

title: italian meat balls(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix all together until well mixed and formed into 1 inch balls. Drop into simmering tomato sauce. Simmer gently for up to 1 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Fix stuffing according to box directions.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Put layer of stuffing over chicken.
Pour 2 cups broth over stuffing.
Put soup, undiluted, over the top.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry tree cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
You may frost, if desired.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cookie sheet chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the flour and sugar in a very large bowl.
Take a saucepan and add the Crisco, cocoa, water and margarine.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Stir well.
Add the buttermilk, eggs (slightly beaten), vanilla and baking soda and mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook first 3 items until slightly thick.
Pour over apples cut very thin in pie crust and cover with second crust.
Cook until brown.
Immediately sprinkle Equal and cinnamon on top while pie is hot.

title: touchdown chili
directions: Take time out to tackle a bowl of this red hot chili.
Just saute onion and bell pepper.
Add beef and cook until browned. Drain.
Mix in other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture reaches 234° (soft ball) on a candy thermometer.
Remove from the heat; stir in marshmallow cream, white chocolate chips and nuts until marshmallow cream and chips are melted.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish.
Cool before cutting.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers and onion in a bowl.
Mix together the remaining ingredients in a jar.
Shake until blended.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until half done in a large pot.
In a bowl, empty contents of cream of chicken soup. Dilute with 3/4 can of water.
Mix well. Spread broccoli into shallow baking dish (9 1/2 x 13-inch).
Pour chicken soup evenly over broccoli.
Prepare the stuffing according to directions on package. Spread stuffing over broccoli.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese (if desired). Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Guaranteed to be a hit!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until creamy.
Spread on a pizza pan.	Brown the hamburg (I always add a little taco sauce while cooking).

I put it in a strainer to drain the grease off. When cool enough to handle spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Then layer with chopped lettuce, spread cheese on top of that, and then chopped tomato.
Serve with taco sauce along side and a bag of Tostitos.

title: apple butter
directions: Put apples with skins on in a tin can in the evening.
Add Karo and sugar on top; put lid on and don't uncover in the morning.
Put it on the stove; cook 3 hours.
Take it off through a colander. Add spice and it's ready to can.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Add salt, eggs, milk and melted butter to Bisquick; stir.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, blot with paper towel.
Serves 12.
(Can be frozen after baking.)

title: green chile cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend together first 7 ingredients.
Mix in blender; pour into bowl and add cheese, chilies and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 days.

title: wassail punch
directions: Combine all in heavy pan and boil for 10 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add lemon juice and orange juice.
When cool, add orange sherbet and mix well; then add mandarin oranges and bananas.
Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix baking powder, flour, salt and sugar.
Mix beaten egg, mashed ripe bananas, can milk and melted shortening in a small bowl.
Then add to flour mixture.
Mix quickly, but thoroughly. Put in prepared pan (floured and greased).
Bake at 350° until bread shrink from sides of pan about 50 minutes.
Let stand five minutes before turning out.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: pineapple-coconut icing
directions: Combine butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Cook until thick. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Good for a coconut or pineapple cake.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 9-inch round 1 1/2 inches deep serving dish, layer the chili on the bottom of the pan.
Then sprinkle with the chiles, green onions and black olives.
Cut the cream cheese into small chunks and scatter over the mixture.
Cover with shredded sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: see's fudge
directions: Put chocolate chips, margarine, vanilla, marshmallow cream and chopped nuts in a large bowl.
Put sugar and Pet milk in a 3 or 4-quart pan.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over contents in bowl. Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into 10 x 16-inch pan.
Let stand 8 hours.

title: cindy carter's potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, onions and potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Place on top of casserole and cook 3 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bee-bop bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place granola in a plastic bag and crush lightly with rolling pin.
In a large bowl, combine granola, oats, almonds, raisins or chocolate pieces, flour, coconut and wheat germ.
In another bowl, stir together the egg, honey, brown sugar, margarine and milk.
Add to dry mixture, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake 36 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned.
Cool pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: lemon dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In medium bowl, stir together the 2 Tbsp. of sugar with 1 cup of flour. Cut into the 1/3 c. of butter until mixture is coarse crumbs. Press firmly into the bottom of 9X9-inch baking dish. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Set aside to cool. In the same bowl, stir together the sugar, salt and baking powder. Add the eggs and vanilla, mix well. Stir in coconut and chopped nuts until everything is coated. Spread mixture evenly over baked crust. Return to oven; bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes. Prepare icing, pour and spread over the top of bars as soon as they come out of oven. Cool 15 minutes before cutting bars.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, mix dry pudding and jello and the 2 1/2 cups cold water.
Stir over heat until it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Put berries in pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Chill until set and serve with dab of Cool Whip.

title: beef stew
directions: Slice onion; peel and dice potatoes.
Peel and slice carrot. Drain green beans.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Prepare packages of pudding as per instructions on box. Spread chocolate pudding on bottom layer of pie.
Slice bananas on top of chocolate pudding.
Pour banana pudding over bananas. Cover banana pudding with whipped topping.
Chill and serve cold.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: In 1-quart glass bowl, combine chips with Eagle Brand milk and salt.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 3 minutes.
Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square dish.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely at room temperature.

title: banana pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine 1/2 cup sugar, the flour and salt.
Add 1 whole beaten egg and the three egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Over simmering water, cook, uncovered, stirring constantly, about 15 minutes, until thickened.
Stir in vanilla.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 11 ingredients and mix well. Transfer to a greased 1 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serves 4.

title: cheese-sausage balls(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Place cheese in top of double boiler. Melt over hot water. Place sausage, Bisquick and melted cheese in large mixing bowl; mix well. Shape into small balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. May be frozen before baking.

title: luncheon salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve on tomatoes and lettuce.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In a large mixer bowl, place instant pudding, sour cream, milk and orange peel.
Beat at low speed until thick and well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, fold in whipped cream.

title: dried fruit
directions: Pour vinegar and sugar over fruit; let stand for 1 hour.
Cook slowly until it is cooked down like regular dried fruit would be when you cook it.
Put in jar while hot and seal.
It may also be frozen.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package; drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain again.
In a large bowl, combine green bell pepper, celery, green onions, pimientos, black olives, peas and cheese. Mix well.
Add drained spaghetti and combine.
In small bowl, combine juice (lemon or lime), salad oil and mayonnaise.
Add to vegetable-spaghetti mixture.
May be served right away or covered and chilled before serving.
(Can use Kraft cheese or Casino Monterey Jack).

title: dreamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix according to directions; set aside.
Combine cream cheese and lemon juice; beat until smooth. Stir in milk, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping and pie filling.
Place about 24 paper baking cups in muffin pans. Spoon mixture into cups; cover and freeze.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and 4 cups flour in large bowl.
Add 2 1/2 cups hot water (temperature on yeast package).
Mix well and add other cup of flour.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except tortillas; mix well. Spread 1/3 cup of ham mixture on each tortilla, covering entire surface. Gently roll up each tortilla, jelly roll fashion. Wrap each roll tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.

title: sugar frosted flake cookies
directions: Beat sugar, brown sugar, oil, oleo and eggs.
Add oatmeal, Frosted Flakes, flour, salt and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: weight watchers cheese cake
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water and cool throughly.
In blender, put pineapple, cottage cheese, gelatin and 1/4 cup of the pineapple juice.
Blend on medium speed until light and fluffy. Pour into mold sprayed with Pam or lightly oiled and let set.

title: coffee can pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 4 (1 pound) coffee cans and flour.
Fill cans half full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 2 sticks butter.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Set aside.
Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder.
Pour over butter.
Pour pie filling over top (any fruit pie filling).
Do not mix layers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix together well the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add the dry ingredients and beat for 3 minutes on medium.
Add pumpkin last. Bake in three 9-inch pans at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost with buttercream frosting.

title: moma dunham's mayonnaise cake and chocolate frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Do not use mixer.
Hand beat until smooth.
Pour into already greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, depending on oven.
The cake is done when a toothpick comes out clean.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Place sliced fruit in a 9 x 2-inch round pan or baking dish. Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour together and sprinkle over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Sift together in bowl 1 cup flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add shortening and blend.
Add milk and egg and stir until thoroughly blended.
Drop by tablespoon over fruit, arranging in a circle, leaving center open.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix with sour cream.
Pour in casserole dish and top with dressing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green mountain rice(from marcliff poultry farm, monroe, north carolina)
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown. In bowl, blend together cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and mix well.
Stir in cooked rice, onion and parsley.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Mix and add to juice and bring to boil for 45 minutes.
Place in hot jars and process.

title: double cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Thaw cherries; drain, reserving juices. Mix sugar, tapioca and cornstarch in saucepan; add 2/3 cup reserved tart cherry juice and 1/3 cup reserved sweet cherry juice.
Mix well.
Cook over high heat until thickened; cool.

title: fast rising rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water to which sugar has been added.
In large bowl stir together flour, dry milk and salt. Making well in center, add 2 cups water, yeast mixture, eggs and salad oil in that order.
Stir until well mixed, adding more flour, if needed to make soft dough.
Cover; allow to rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead a few times to make dough easy to handle.
Pinch off smooth round pieces about egg size; arrange 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Cover lightly with clean towel; allow to rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Dough may be used for cinnamon or other kinds of rolls.

title: round steak stew
directions: Cook in pot with 1 cup water until done.

title: laura's blue margaritas
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until slushy.
Pour into glasses and serve.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add zucchini, then flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased pan in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: lamb and celery khoresh
directions: Fry the onion in 2 Tbsp. of the butter in a large saucepan or flameproof casserole for 3-4 minutes.
Add the meat and cook for 2-3 minutes until browned, stirring frequently, then stir in the turmeric, cinnamon and salt and pepper.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes.
When potatoes are tender, drain and mash.
Add the chopped up boiled eggs.
Dice onion and add to potatoes.
Add the pickles, mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar.
Stir all ingredients together until mixed well.
Add salt to taste. More mayonnaise or mustard may be added if desired.
Garnish with paprika.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, confectioners sugar, nuts and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in finely granulated sugar.
Moisten cut side of cherries in corn syrup and press one on each sugar-coated rum ball.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 36.

title: banana split sunday
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine; press in pan and chill.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over crumbs. Slice 3 or 4 bananas over batter.
Drain pineapple (crushed) and spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix pastry dough and pie pan.
Beat eggs until lemon color. Add sugar and beat well.
Add whole milk and nutmeg.
Mix well. Then pour in unbaked pastry shell.
Will make one deep or 2 shallow pies.
Bake in oven at 375°.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Into a large bowl, sift the flour, baking powder, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add the shortening and cut in with a pastry blender.
In a small bowl, mix the yeast with the warm water, stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add the buttermilk.
Pour liquid mixture into the flour mixture and mix.
Put out onto a floured board and knead well.
(Mixture may be kept in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.)

title: low-fat lasagne
directions: Mix cooked and drained noodles with cottage cheese and sour cream.
Pour spaghetti sauce over drained hamburger and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place in an 11 x 15-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour, sugar and beer together with fork and hands.
Pat into pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter; pour over top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in skillet, cover and simmer with a little water about one hour.
Saute peppers and onions until tender.
Add cherry tomatoes, gherkins and pineapple chunks.
Mix together cornstarch, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and brown sugar. Add to vegetables and meat, cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: ham ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Chill until almost firm.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans, coating well. Serve with crackers or assorted breads.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain on paper towel.
Combine with other ingredients.
Spray PAM on 9 X 12 pan.
Line with slices of bread. Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 for approximately 1 hour until golden brown.

title: phyllo chicken
directions: Brush sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with melted butter. Place 1 sheet phyllo on bottom.
Brush with butter.
Repeat 5 more sheets (keep remaining phyllo covered with wax paper to prevent drying out.)
In bowl, combine chicken, bacon, broccoli and cheese. Spread over phyllo.
In another bowl, whisk eggs, cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with 1 phyllo and brush with butter.
Repeat remaining phyllo, top and butter.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift together cinnamon, flour, baking soda and salt and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs and mix well. Stir in apples, milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Beat in sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not double recipe.

title: creamed chicken
directions: In saucepan cook onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Add chicken broth and 1/3 cup milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in chicken.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture is boiling.
Pour over mashed potatoes.

title: preston payne's chili
directions: Slow cook for "quite a while."

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add and mix sugar, vanilla, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Then add and mix apple and nuts. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: belgian potatoes
directions: Put the potatoes into a baking dish.
Pour over them half the melted butter to which the seasonings have been added.
Bake in a hot oven until potatoes are half cooked.
Stir lightly; add remainder of butter mixture and continue to bake until potatoes are tender and the edges are brown and crisp.
Serves 6.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together the 2 cups of flour and confectioners sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture clings together. Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion and green pepper and continue cooking until onion is soft.
Drain excess fat.
Put canned tomatoes in blender and "chop" briefly.
Add to meat mixture, along with corn, olives and garlic salt to taste, chili powder and cheese.
Heat through.
Line bottom of ungreased casserole with one-half of cooked mush.
Add meat mixture and top with remaining mush.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Crust:
Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in 8 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir while baking.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: With electric mixer, mix first 3 ingredients until creamy. Add milk.
Mix again until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze.
Take out and enjoy.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening over low heat; add brown sugar and beat well. Let cool.
Add eggs and blend.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Spread in a greased 15 x 12 x 1-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: caramel frosting for spice cake
directions: Melt butter in pan with brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes on low.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil, then cool.
Add the powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in greased and floured, large, rimmed cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with flour and powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel and let cool.
Be sure to roll it up while still warm.

title: shrimp salad
directions: If shrimp are large, cut into halves or quarters.

Mix shrimp, celery, eggs and pickles together lightly with mayonnaise to which the catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper have been added. Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with sliced tomatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla, butter and syrup.
Mix thoroughly and add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust that has been prebaked for 5 minutes in oven.
Bake slowly at 300° for 1 hour.
For 2 pies, double all ingredients, except use 5 eggs.

title: brandy slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well in a large container.
Store in freezer, mixing well every day for 3 days.
Mix 1/2 glass of slush with sour soda.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix with electric mixer in order given.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. This makes a loaf pan.
Double recipe and it will make a medium tube pan.

title: swope bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 loaf pans. Combine both flours, sugar and salt.
Mix milk with soda.
Stir into flour mixture.
Put in pans.
Put into oven and reduce heat to 350°. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done in center when tested with toothpick. Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: big mouth stew
directions: In a small saucepan, simmer the mixed vegetables until done. While they are cooking, melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a deep frypan. Slice the kielbasa and then quarter each of the slices so there are 4 bite size pieces. Brown the kielbasa in the butter. Then add the cream of mushroom soup to the meat and butter, then add the milk and blend it all together, making a cream sauce. Add the vegetables; blend it all together and serve over rice. Use milk to the consistency you like.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes and use on spareribs, hot dogs or chicken.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Press flattened crescent rolls into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside until cool.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and chill. Before serving, add ginger ale and orange slice for garnish.
Serves 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the applesauce, egg, oil and honey.
Set the bowl aside.
In a medium bowl, combine the whole wheat and white flours, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add this to applesauce mixture, stirring just to moisten the dry ingredients.
Stir in the raisins and divide the batter amoung 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake the muffins in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, celery, green peppers and garlic in butter.
Add to tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; heat to boiling.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Serve over wild rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish and top with "Tater Topping" or Mrs. Dash.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and fat together over low heat.
Cool slightly. Mix sugar with eggs.
Stir chocolate mixture into eggs gradually. Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Add chocolate mixture.
Spread batter in an 8-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until crust is shiny and brownies begin to shrink from pan.

title: italian chicken bundles
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken and onion in hot oil over medium heat until chicken is no longer pink and onion is tender. In a large mixing bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, oregano, nutmeg and lemon juice. Stir in chicken and onions. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Lightly grease 8 (10-ounce) custard cups with some of the melted margarine or butter. Line each dish with an egg roll wrapper. Divide chicken mixture among the 8 dishes. Fold the ends of each wrapper over the top of the chicken mixture, sealing to make a bundle. Brush with remaining melted margarine or butter. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until tops are golden.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: In a medium size skillet, heat oil to about 300°.
Pass tortillas into hot oil for a few seconds to soften and seal. Remove carefully and set aside (do this just prior to final assembly).
Fill softened tortillas with the chicken filling and 1 to 2 tablespoons of the sauce.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a casserole.
Pour the remainder of the sauce over the top and top with cheese.
Place in a 350° oven for 5 to 8 minutes or just long enough to melt the cheese.
Serve with sour cream, guacamole or salsa.
Makes 8 enchiladas.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in reserved ham.
Reserve 1/3 of ham to roll.

title: hobbit seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in, one at a time, the 5 eggs. When creamy, fold in the flour, seed and salt.
Spoon into one large or two small loaf pans which have been buttered and floured. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in water and vanilla.
Add chocolate, flour and dash of salt; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until done, about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except reserved margarine and bread crumbs.
Put in well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and pour margarine around top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato dumplings
directions: For Dumplings:
Combine flour, egg and salt and mix with fork. Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water until mixture holds together. Roll out on well floured surface and cut into 2 x 2-inch squares and set aside.
Cut potatoes in bite size pieces.
Boil bacon in kettle (I use Dutch oven) and add potatoes to boiling water and cook until tender.
Slowly add dumplings, stirring constantly so they don't stick.
Reduce heat and cook 25 to 30 minutes and serve.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Fry patties in a little oil until light brown.
Fry at medium heat.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots.
Let stand until thickened.
Add carrots.
Chill until firm.

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine, slowly beat in sugars.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Sift flour with soda; add oats.
Stir into first mixture.
Stir in peanuts and chocolate bits, mixing well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk gradually.
Add vanilla. Measure bread cubes and put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour egg-milk over bread cubes.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: asparagus roll ups
directions: Place a slice of cheese on top of each ham slice.
Place 3 asparagus spears on each cheese slice.
Roll up tightly and place seam side down in a buttered 8 by 8-inch casserole dish side by side.
Top each roll up evenly with sour cream and salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Remove and discard skin from chicken.
Boil chicken in water (salted or unsalted, as you prefer) until done; remove chicken, reserving 2 2/3 cups broth.
Debone and cut up chicken in small pieces; set aside.
Strain broth and add mushroom soup, mixing well; set aside.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup of mixture for garnish.

title: throw together banana pudding
directions: Put a layer of wafers, a layer of bananas, a layer of Cool Whip, etc. until you fill a large bowl.
Cook vanilla pudding until almost getting thick.
Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Be sure it soaks all the way through.
Let set overnight (do not refrigerate).
Cover top with Cool Whip next day before eating.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Slice onions on bottom of casserole.
Slice potatoes over onions.
Salt and pepper.
Crumble meat over potatoes.
Dice celery over meat.
Sprinkle rice over celery.
Pour the beans and then the soup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and fruit juice; mix until smooth. Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: fish patties
directions: In medium-size bowl, mix all ingredients.
Form into hamburger size patties.
Fry in greased skillet until brown on both sides.

title: cool whip icing
directions: Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese with sugar.
Stir in pineapple.
Spread on cake and top with coconut.

title: pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisy icing
directions: Cook together. Spread over yellow cake while icing is still hot.

title: brendon's special sandwich
directions: Slice hot dog diagonally (let Mom do this).
Fry lightly in Silverstone or nonstick surface frypan until lightly browned (Mom should do this, too).
Add plenty of catsup (you can do this if your Mom lets you).
Add chopped or finely sliced onions (you don't want to do this, let Mom).
Fry until all cooked, but not burned. Serve over bed of hot rice and eat!
(You and Mom can do this!)

title: southern fried chicken
directions: In medium size bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, pepper and paprika.
In a small bowl, pour the milk.
Heat skillet and add the oil.
When it's hot, dip each piece of chicken first into the milk, and then into the dry ingredients.
Brown chicken on each side according to your taste.
After browned on both sides, simmer on each side for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: pineapple bar cake
directions: With electric mixer, mix butter, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and soda which have been sifted together.
Last add the pineapple and nuts.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While still warm, sprinkle the top with powdered sugar.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Pour juices and water into a 12 cup percolated.
Place brown sugar and next 3 ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Yields 7 cups.

title: new england seafood chowder
directions: Saute salt pork until brown.
Remove, saving 1 tablespoon fat. Saute onion, celery and green pepper until soft.
Add flour. Stir well.
Add water or fish broth.
Stir until boiling.
Add potatoes, spices and fish fillets.
Bring to boil on low heat. When fillets are flaky, remove and break into pieces.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add any shellfish, shelled.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Add fish pieces.
Combine milk and evaporated milk (or half and half).
Add to pot.
Add salt pork.
Heat.
Do not boil.
Add sherry.
Taste for seasoning.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding as
directed
on
package using 1 1/2 cups fruit juice from	pineapple
and chunky fruit instead of milk. Cool. When cool, fold
in fruit; put in glass bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix well; refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with a damp cloth.
Remove stems; leave caps intact.
Chop up stems; brush caps with butter, set aside.

title: golden salad
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen orange juice.
Stir until melted.
Stir in pineapple and oranges; pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and chill until set. Prepare pudding according to package directions using only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread over top of set gelatin.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fabulous cheese dip
directions: Mix cheeses and dressing well.
Add green onions and green peppers.
Set overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables and/or crackers.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip. Makes a nice ice pie.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain and rinse under cold water; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt, vinegar, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, yogurt mixture and vegetables.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly and serve cold.
Makes 4 servings with 269 calories per serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and bring to a boil for 1 minute the first three ingredients.
If making on a rainy day, boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir well and add the oats.
Drop on wax paper.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: nacho dip
