directions: Brown hamburger, season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain and return to stove.
On low heat add cheese dips and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until all cheese melts.
Can be put in crock-pot to keep warm while serving.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place one pie crust in bottom of deep dish pie plate.
Mix above ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Top with other pie crust and flute around the sides.
Make three slits in top crust. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°, then increase oven to 450° and bake an additional 10 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: fat man's misery
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together melted margarine, wafers or crackers and nuts until crumbly.
Press in bottom of dish, 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs in 3-quart bowl until well mixed.
Stir in next 6 ingredients until well blended.
Measure spices into a cup, add boiling water and stir to a smooth paste, then stir thoroughly into pumpkin mixture.
Turn mixture into pastry-lined pan.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to slow (300°), opening oven a minute so heat drops rapidly to 300°.
Bake about 25 minutes longer or until custard tests done.
Remove to cake rack to cool to lukewarm before cutting.

title: meta's dessert
directions: Roll vanilla wafers and make crumbs.
Pour 3/4 on bottom of pan.
Take oleo, butter and sugar, vanilla and beat until fluffy then add eggs one at a time and beat 1 minute until you use the 3 then spread on top of crumbs.
Take and drain crushed pineapple and put on top of egg mixture.
Then slice bananas on top of pineapple. Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine, pecans and sugar.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan or two 9-inch pie pans for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Butter a Bundt pan.
Place roll dough in it and pour stick of melted margarine over it.
Mix dry pudding, brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle over the top of the rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Empty onto serving plate immediately.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Drain mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients. Cover with foil; bake until rice is done.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a Pyrex pan (9 x 13-inch). Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Shut off oven; let the cake set in oven for 1 hour.
Cover with cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In a bowl, mix beef, water and taco mix.
Add corn, peppers and tomato sauce; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Prepare corn muffin mix and add 1/2 can of onions to it.
Spoon muffin mixture around outer edge of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and cheese and bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; remove from pan and set aside.
Add celery to remaining butter; stir until crisp and tender.
Blend in flour, gradually.
Add barbecue sauce and mix well.
Add tomatoes, onions and salt.
Mix well until thick.
Cover and simmer fifteen minutes.
Add shrimp and mushrooms.
Cook ten more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken broccoli dinner
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Leave in large pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Mix undiluted soup, mushrooms, chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Spoon over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put onion rings on.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; coat lightly with flour. In large skillet in hot oil, lightly brown chicken on both sides; remove and set aside. Add mushrooms, onions and garlic to skillet; cook and stir until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Return chicken to skillet; spoon sauce over to coat. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until tender. Yield: 4 servings.

title: scotch-a-roo's
directions: Mix Karo syrup and sugar; bring to boil, then remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies; mix well.
Pat into greased cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread melted topping onto Rice Krispie mixture.
Let topping firm a little before cutting into squares.

title: onion cheese quiche
directions: Always bake pie crust first for about 8 minutes at 425° before adding the filling.

title: poppy seed dressing(this recipe goes great with all types of fruit)
directions: You must start with sugar and then vinegar, then you can go on with recipe.
Beat with electric mixer; if too thick or grainy you may add 1 tablespoon of hot water (no more).

title: sausage and rice
directions: Crumble sausage and brown. Drain. Add green pepper, celery and onion to sausage. Continue cooking until vegetables are tender. Add slivered almonds and reserve some for garnish. In another pan, combine soup, water and rice. Simmer 20 minutes. Add salt and butter. Stir well. Combine rice and sausage mixture. Put in 3-quart greased baking dish. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft; blend with sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Whip
the cream; add vanilla and powdered sugar to the whipped cream mixture.
Fold whipped cream mixture into cheese mixture.
Grease a large rectangular pan lightly with mayonnaise and pour mixture into pan.
Freeze at least 6 hours before serving.
Cut into serving portions and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Cut off both ends; leave 2 layers of shucks on ear.
Cook in microwave 8 minutes.
Take out, run cold water over corn, then shuck.
Put in aluminum foil with butter until ready to eat.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Boil separately in sugar and salt for 3 minutes the carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and zucchini.
Brown in 1/2 to 1 cube of butter, the onions and mushrooms.
Butter bottom of casserole.
Put half of the onion-mushroom mixture in casserole.
Layer vegetables on top.
Put the rest of the onion mixture on top of vegetables.

title: chili for a crowd(serves 40 people)
directions: Brown
and
drain
ground meat.
Stir into meat chopped onions and bell peppers.
Pour Worcestershire sauce generously over meat. Add
onion salt, garlic salt, celery salt, pepper, Tabasco and chili powder to taste.
The more generous you are with these seasonings,
the spicier the chili.
Add about 1/2 cup parsley flakes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring often to avoid sticking.

title: excellent pudding
directions: Put in pudding dish or 2-quart casserole.
Steam 2 hours and serve with whipped cream.

title: prune waldorf salad
directions: Soak prunes in water just enough to cover, then heat until prunes plump out or swell.
Drain and chill thoroughly.
Combine prunes with celery and apple.
Stir in enough dressing to moisten. Line salad bowl with lettuce leaves and pour mixture on top. Garnish with walnuts.

title: no-fat vegetable soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to boil, then add cabbage, carrots, celery and onion.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Add tomatoes, bean sprouts and green beans.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in water.
Add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: south-of-the-border casserole
directions: Brown meat, add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Alternate layers of meat mixture, tortillas and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole, ending with cheese. Bake at 320° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 or more servings.

title: creamy glaze doughnut topping
directions: Melt butter or
in saucepan.
Blend in confectioners' sugar and vanilla.
Stir in water, 1 tablespoon at a time until glaze is of proper consistency.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce mixture, uncooked lasagna noodles and cottage cheese until all is used.
Put Mozzarella and/or Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt; toss and let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and green peppers.
Let stand 2 minutes; drain.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to boil. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Allow to cool.
Put in freezer cups and seal, label and date.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger with onion until done (browned and crumbly). Combine all other ingredients.
Then add the hamburger mixture and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir once or twice while baking.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except can of icing.
Bake as directed on cake mix, maybe a little longer.
Ice with can or package of cherry chip icing mix.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl beat cake mix and eggs. Fold in pie filling. Spread in greased sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: favorite beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef with celery, onion and bell pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes. In a large casserole, combine beans and brown sugar.
Stir in beef mixture and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: best brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients, beating well.
Bake in an 11 x 16-inch greased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese patties
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients; let stand a few minutes to season and thicken.
Drop mixture from tablespoon and brown patties slowly on both sides.
Place in casserole dish and cover with Mushroom Gravy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce.
Make a layer in flat dish. Brown beef; season to taste.
Add chilies and mushroom soup; mix well.
Spread 1/3 of meat mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of onion and grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until heated.

title: oyster soup
directions: Brown salt pork until crisp; add onions and garlic.
Cook until nice and browned.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Stir well. Cover and let simmer on low fire for about 1 hour, stirring several times.
Add oysters, liquid and about 2 quarts water and bring to a boil on high heat.
Lower to medium heat and cook for about 30 minutes.
Add spaghetti.
Return to a boil; add the green onions and parsley.
Continue to cook until spaghetti is tender (about 15 minutes longer).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
This soup is better if cooked early, then reheated just before serving, allowing the flavors to blend together.

title: orange popsicles
directions: Will also need aluminum foil, ice cube tray and popsicle sticks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Combine next 10 ingredients and add chicken.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan; top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 can French fried onions on top, then bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: orange sauce for ham
directions: Combine marmalade, juice, mustard, ginger and ground cloves. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stud ham with whole cloves.
Bake with half the sauce over ham.
Add raisins after baking.	Serve sauce with ham.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together except onion rings.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Top with a little more cheese and add the fried onion rings.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken fettuccine
directions: Mix mayo, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Spoon over 2 to 3 pounds of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in large bowl.
Add oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Spray Bundt pan with cooking spray.
Pour batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 1/2 hour. Remove from pan.

title: grandma mcconnell's good old fashioned teacakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll and cut on floured surface.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: day before mashed potatoes
directions: Boil a large pot of salted water.
Drop in potatoes and cook until tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain potatoes and put in large mixing bowl with 1 tbsp. butter.
Mix on low speed until potatoes are smooth.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, onion powder, salt and pepper and beat on low speed to blend.
Coat a 9 x 13 in. baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread potato mixture into the dish and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: hal's soleful greens
directions: Cover ham hock with water.
Boil on medium heat until tender. Pick and wash greens under running water.
Add greens to ham hock pot.
Cook on medium heat until vegetable are tender.
Serve with hot sauce or chow chow.

title: prize winning key-lime cake or "lime-light cake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place dry ingredients (first 6) into mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13- x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until tests done.

title: dill cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour over cucumbers and tomatoes, lifting vegetables to allow sauce to cover all layers. Chill.

title: indiana-style corn dogs
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients, except hot dogs and oil.
Pour mixture into tall glass.
Skewer hot dogs with wooden skewers; dip in mixture.
Deep fry at 375° until golden (about 2 minutes). Drain on paper towels.

title: *bessie williams' corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using white or yellow corn, as you desire.
Place in casserole and put in oven in a pan of water. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: baked artichoke spread
directions: Drain and chop artichokes. Add other ingredients and blend in ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers or blend.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine; gradually add sugar while beating.
Beat until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy.
Add crumbs, alternating with milk; mix well.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch tube cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: honey baked biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line cookie sheet with a piece of foil. Place flour, baking powder and cinnamon into mixing bowl and blend.
Add butter to flour mixture and work in with your fingers. Butter will disappear into flour.
Add honey, milk and egg to mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon until thoroughly mixed.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven.
For Minute rice, bake 30 to 45 minutes.
For regular rice, bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: boston baked beans with tomato sauce
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Wash and parboil with soda in boiling water until they are barely tender.
Rinse.
Put in bean pot or casserole. Mix in all the seasonings and barley, placing the pork at the bottom.
Cover with boiling water.
Cover and cook very slowly for 6 hours.
Renew with water as needed. Important:
During the last two hours, draw the pork to the surface. Score and let it brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together; serve with fruit.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Add fresh water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook 45 minutes.
Drain beans and rinse in hot water. Place beans in greased casserole.
Combine other ingredients and pour over beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian crescent zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add spices and mix well.
Mix eggs and cheese in separate bowl.
Butter a large pie pan or quiche dish. Arrange crescent rolls to make a crust.
Spread a thin layer of mustard on crust.
Mix vegetables with eggs and cheese and pour onto crust.
Makes a large pie.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: larry's apple cake
directions: Use a heavy 12-inch cast-iron skillet.
Coat the sides liberally with nonstick spray.
Preheat skillet in a 350° oven. In a large bowl, mix together with a wire whisk the sugar, flour and milk until thoroughly blended.
(Do not overwork; you want it smooth and free of lumps.)
In a separate 12-inch skillet, heat 4 tablespoons of butter to sizzling.
Add the apples, apple pie spice and cinnamon; quickly cook them until they soften.
(Just a few minutes; don't overcook, they should be crunchy.)

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Add onion and salt to meat and press into a casserole dish. Add vegetables and soups.
Stand Tater Tots up, pressing them into the meat, covering entire top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chuck's specialty muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour muffin pan (be sure not to get any grease or flour on the top of the pan).
Mix all ingredients together until mixed well.
Pour into muffin tins. Place in oven and bake for 15 minutes or until done.

title: special occasion
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare shallow baking dish or pan by spraying lightly with Pam cooking spray.
Carefully wash flounder fillets; rinse in diluted lemon juice (one part lemon, three parts juice).
Pat dry with paper towels.
Rub with olive oil; season with salt and pepper.
Place 4 fillets in prepared baking dish. Combine stuffing mix, chopped vegetables, crab meat and egg; mixture will be loose.
Spoon on top of flounder in baking dish. Carefully place remaining fillets on top of stuffing, pressing ends of top and bottom fillets together.
Using a knife, cut a 2-inch slit in top fillets.
If desired, garnish with paprika, parsley, baby shrimp and any remaining stuffing.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until stuffing is lightly browned.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with the juice of half a lemon.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Boil broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix chopped broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese together; place into greased deep dish pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth for 1 minute; pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: texas rice
directions: Put margarine in a heavy pan.
Pan fry onion and pepper until onion is slightly browned.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry sausage
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Remove and drain.
In same pan, cook vegetables until tender.
Add sausage and cashew nuts.
Cook 2 minutes until warm.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip the cream and add sugar and pineapple.
Mix all of the ingredients together; spread into serving pan.
Cover and freeze.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine rhubarb, strawberries, sugar and flour well.
Place mixture in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish or 8 x 8 x 2-inch or whatever works.

title: lazy day chicken
directions: Mix Pepsi and ketchup together.
Add chicken and simmer until done.
For larger amounts of chicken, just double Pepsi and ketchup.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Choose plump potatoes without many roots and without cut places on it.
Wash potatoes good and dry them.
With your hands very lightly butter or oil the potatoes.

title: pull ko kee(korean barbecue beef)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except beef.
Add meat and let stand for a few hours.
Remove meat from sauce and broil over hot coals.
Meat may be broiled in a broiler or in a skillet on top of range.

title: imo's delight
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Place in an oblong baking pan. Mix together milk and pudding. Add ice cream. Mix until smooth and place over graham crackers.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Remove and spread topping 1-inch thick.
Sprinkle with crushed candy.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil and cool, but not too cool, the sugar, cider vinegar and corn oil.
Set aside.
Chop or cut the celery and radishes. Drain the sauerkraut, rinse and redrain.
Mix all vegetables and pour mixture overall.
Let stand at least 4 hours or fix a day ahead.

title: cheese dumplings
directions: Blend cottage cheese, 1/2 cup mashed potatoes, 2 beaten eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and cinnamon; let stand.
Blend the flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, baking powder, 1 egg and 1/2 cup mashed potatoes. Add enough cold milk to hold dough together.
Take walnut size portion and roll into pancake size circle.
Place tablespoon cheese mixture in circle.
Fold in half and pinch closed.
Drop into boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not crowd.
Remove with strainer spoon.
Serve with melted butter and browned bread crumbs.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat butter or margarine until melted. Stir in brown sugar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar.
Place saucepan of frosting in bowl of cold water; beat until smooth and spreading consistency.
If frosting becomes too stiff, add more milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Blend together the other 3 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Gently fold the beaten egg whites into the cheese mixture.
Fill the dusted muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: almolgmasia cake
directions: Mix together and beat well. Makes 4 layers.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix Rice Chex, butter and sugar (3 tablespoons) and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then cool.
Mix Cool Whip, 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved.
Add berries.
Spread over Cool Whip layer.
Store in fridge.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: hard labor creek chicken
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes or so.
Habinero pepper sauce will make it extremely hot.
This recipe is also very low in fat.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind and drain pepper.
Mix sugar, peppers and vinegar.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Take from heat.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Add Certo and let stand 10 minutes.
Skim and pour into sterilized jars and seal.
You may use green food coloring.

title: tostadas
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Oregano leaves and cumin; mix well.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes stirring occasionally until thoroughly heated and flavors are well blended.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat Dream Whip and 1 cup of milk on high for 7 minutes (should be fluffy); then add rest of milk, vanilla and pudding. Beat on low.
Pour into pie shell and let set.

title: chocolate kentucky pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pie crust in freezer while you make filling.
Beat the eggs with a whisk until just blended. Gradually add 1/2 the sugar.
Add cornstarch to remaining 1/2 of the sugar, stirring to remove lumps.
Blend into egg mixture.
Add and stir in brandy and butter.
Pour this into pie shell that you have first added nuts and chocolate bits to.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve at room temperature with whipped cream.

title: caramel torte
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add sugar and continue beating. Add rusk crumbs, nuts, baking powder and vanilla; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.

title: steamed pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk and molasses to lard and mix. Combine mixtures and mix well.
Pour into a cloth and steam for 2 1/2 hours.
Raisins may be added.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes and stir until thickened.
Cut cheese in chunks and melt in the tomatoes.
Stir well.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, salt and red pepper.

title: zucchini-carrot dish
directions: Cook zucchini; drain.
Cook onions and carrots in 4 tablespoons butter.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups croutons, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini; put into casserole dish.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and 1 cup croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Quarter and drain artichokes.
Slice mushrooms and saute in butter.
Put artichokes and mushrooms in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine next four ingredients and spread over vegetables. Sprinkle with last three ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: saltine cracker cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with Pam.
Spread crackers, side by side, on cookie sheet to fill sheet.
Bring butter and sugar to boil. Boil for 3 minutes, then pour over crackers.
Bake 8 minutes only at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread melted chocolate chips over crackers.
Let cool and break off into pieces.
Store in wax papered tin in refrigerator.

title: herb coated radishes
directions: Place radishes in a small saucepan.
Cover with salted water. Simmer over low heat, covered, until tender (10 to 12 minutes). Drain well.
Add butter, thyme, basil, fennel seed and white pepper.
Stir over medium heat until radishes are well coated. Serve immediately.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a salad bowl, toss together the cabbage, carrot, green or red sweet pepper and green onion.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over pasta and toss.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Gradually beat oil into wine or cider.
Stir in the remainder of the ingredients.
Pour marinade over the chicken, cover and chill 2 to 3 hours, turning at least twice.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup with mayonnaise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer 1/2 broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup mixture over top and sprinkle with more cheese.
Heat through at 350°.

title: fat-free salad dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Use as a dressing on green salads and steamed vegetables.
Excellent on steamed broccoli. Keeps in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Seasoned rice vinegar is available in most supermarkets.
Check the vinegar section as well as the Oriental foods section.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, chestnuts, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkish yogurt(yogurt with cucumbers)
directions: Peel, seed and dice cucumbers.
Sprinkle cucumbers with salt. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour off liquid.
Mash garlic in bowl with lemon juice.
Add yogurt, dill and cucumbers; mix well and chill.
Sprinkle with olive oil and mint.
Serve as an appetizer or accompany with a meal.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large plastic pan, place ground beef.
In a bowl, mix the bread slices, egg and milk.
When well mixed, add to the ground beef and mix real well.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper, Accent and 1/2 cup catsup.
Mix together thoroughly.
If mixture is too stiff, add milk.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: buffet carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly and drain.
Cook onion in melted margarine for 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
Layer carrots and Cheddar cheese in 2-quart casserole, beginning and ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over layers and top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon delight pie
directions: Heat over medium heat the margarine, flour and pecans until toasted.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In oil, salt and pepper meat and brown,
with worcestershire sauce and onions.
Drain meat. Mix meat, ketchup, and mustard together.
Grease a 3 qt. baking dish, and spread meat mixture in dish.
Sprinkle cheese on meat mixture and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over top of meat mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: my mother-in-law's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients; then flavor.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter or drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 375° until golden.

title: butterscotch coconut drops
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugars.
Blend in unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients (flour, etc.); mix thoroughly.
Stir in butterscotch morsels and pecans.
Mix well. Chill.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into coconut; roll to coat.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
If desired, top with pecans halves or maraschino cherries.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into small meatballs.
Place in a casserole and pour sauce mix over meatballs.
Cover casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
After 40 minutes, reduce heat and let simmer another hour.
(The longer they simmer, the better they are.)

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and sugar and set aside. In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with apple mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool top with Lemon Glaze.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers, cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs two at a time.
Slowly add milk and
mix well.
Add crushed wafers, nuts and coconut to mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook 1 hour until golden
brown at 325°.

title: stove top rice pudding(good for your heart, bones, nerves and taste)
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil then simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently until pudding thickens.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Stir and cool. Chill before serving.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Chill until consistency of thick syrup. Fold in cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour in mold and chill thoroughly.
May be served on lettuce leaf with or without dressing.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine margarine, cheese and pepper. Add flour a little at a time. Mix well, add pecans and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies last, mixing well. Form into small balls, place on cookie sheet and flatten with a floured fork. Bake in 350 degree oven until light brown about 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Store in covered container, will keep for 2 weeks or more.

title: party punch(serves 30)
directions: Make a syrup of 4 cups of sugar and 2 cups of water.
Boil 3 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, Pet milk, sugar, margarine, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with brown sugar, pecans, flour and softened margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream first 6 ingredients; add flour. Press in 12-inch or 14-inch pizza pan, forming ridge around edge. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes, until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Cool and cut into wedges.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 20 servings.

title: pasta with bell peppers, goat cheese and basil
directions: In a skillet, cook the garlic in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, for 1 minute, add the onion, and cook the mixture, stirring, until the onion is softened.

Add the bell peppers, cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, for 5 minutes or until the peppers are just tender and add the wine and the olives. Boil the wine until it is reduced by half, season the mixture with salt and black pepper, and stir in the basil.
In a kettle of boiling salted water cook the pasta until it is al dente and drain it well, reserving 1/3 cup of the cooking water.

In a serving bowl, whisk two thirds of the goat cheese with the reserved cooking water until the cheese is melted and the mixture is smooth, add the pasta and the bell pepper mixture, and toss the mixture well.
Sprinkle the pasta with the remaining goat cheese. Serves 2.

title: cinnamon fruit and rice squares(yields 6 servings)
directions: In a small saucepan, place water and 1/2 teaspoon of the cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Add rice; return to the boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until rice is tender, about 15 minutes; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups of the orange juice, sugar, cloves and remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Add apples; simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup orange juice and cornstarch.
Stir into saucepan; cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add bananas, grapes, vanilla extract and reserved rice; mix well. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow serving dish.
Cover and chill. Serve cut in squares and topped with yogurt.
Contains 202 calories per portion; contains less than 1 gm fat per portion, 1 mg cholesterol per portion and 1 mg sodium per portion.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and water.
Boil until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites; add syrup mixture.
Add nuts. Make into spoon size balls.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and paprika together. Then stir in corn.
Add beaten eggs.
Drop a tablespoon at a time in hot oil in deep frying pan and cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper and serve hot with butter.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend after each addition in the order listed.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: eclaire dessert
directions: Bring water and butter to boil. Remove from heat and stir in flour. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: rosanne's cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Next add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough for 20 minutes. Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bran muffin refrigerator mix
directions: Beat until creamy:
1 cup shortening, 3 cups sugar.
Add 4 eggs and beat well; 5 1/2 cups flour, 5 tsp soda, 1 tbsp salt and 1 quart buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together; add raisins, optional.
Pour into plastic sealed containers.
Bake whenever you wish in greased muffin tins at 350° for about 15 minutes.
This mix will keep in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball or log and chill for several hours before serving with crackers.

title: banana chocolate drop cookies
directions: Can add whole chocolate chips also, if desired.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Toss berries with 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice. Stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread cake pieces in 9 x 9-inch square pan. Pour yogurt over cake.
Spread evenly.
Pour strawberries over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
To serve, sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Thaw 1 to 2 hours.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes 15 minutes before removing from pans. Cool on wire racks.
Frost with Mother's Famous Icing.

title: easy baked cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Add eggs and mix until blended.
Pour into crust and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Top with topping of your choice. Store leftover cheesecake in the refrigerator.

title: sausage souffle
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Mix cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut and chopped nuts.
Add flour mixed with baking soda.
Add vanilla. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans, bacon, onion, paste, salt, pepper and water for approximately 3 hours on conventional stove.
After 1 1/2 hours, add sausage, broken into small pieces and chili powder.
If you use a crock-pot, add the sausage and chili powder at the beginning.
Serve over rice.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let set for 1 hour, then drain well.
Combine all together; bring to a boil and put in jars.
Cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease your loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat the oleo, egg and sugar until smooth.
Add the bananas and milk; mix well.
Add the flour mixture, beating just until smooth.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into the pan and bake for 1 hour or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: divine muffins
directions: Stir and drop into greased muffin pans.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Peel and chop leeks; all of the white and some of the tender green parts.
Rinse well.
Fry leeks in butter in soup pot on low heat until soft.
Add broth and salt.
Peel and chop potatoes into small pieces.
Add to soup.
Cook 40 minutes on low heat.
Puree entire soup in blender or food processor.
Return to pot and slowly stir in 1 cup milk.
Do not boil.
Serve hot with freshly ground pepper.
(Can thin the soup with more broth if desired.)

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Spread brown sugar in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place biscuits on top of brown sugar.
Pour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn upside-down and serve.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with electric mixer and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips over hot water and spread over mixture.
Cut in small bars.
Refrigerate 15 minutes and enjoy!

title: oysters of the bayou
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter; add oysters.
When edges curl, add oyster liquid and milk; stir; add seasonings.
Fold in bread crumbs.
Place in a 2-quart casserole or individual dishes; sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
This dish may also be served in large pastry shells.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all three ingredients until well blended.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookie down with a fork with a cross design.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
May be frozen. Makes 24 cookies.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine butter (melt), buttermilk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread on top of cake.
May need to add 1 additional cup of powdered sugar to make icing more thick texture.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir baking soda into buttermilk. Add small amount of flour to butter, beating on medium speed, alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl until stiff and fold into cake batter.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake for 45 minutes in 325° oven. Cool and ice.

title: blackberry dumplins
directions: Wash berries. Bring to a boil. Then cut biscuits in strips. Put in cup of sugar. Cook until done.

title: fresh coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy saucepan; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot milk mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Stir 2/3 cup coconut into cooled filling.
Pour filling into pastry shell; chill overnight.
Beat whipping cream until foamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Spread over pie.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until reaching soft ball stage.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Spoon sauce into pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Prepare white yeast dough.
Take piece of dough size of walnut.
Roll into long strip about 6 inches long.
Dip in melted butter, then into Sugar-Cinnamon Mixture.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt together; set aside.
Beat eggs and skim milk; add to flour.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into heated greased muffin tins, filling half full or less.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do NOT open oven for first 30 minutes.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk; sti over low heat until cream cheese in melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: peach cake
directions: Dump peaches in pan with juice. Top with melted butter and coconut. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Bake 325 degrees till done.

title: turner's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, creamed well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to butter mixture and to this add all the cut up fruit and nuts.
Drop batter from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. (Do not overbake.)
Instead of dropping dough, a small piece may be pinched off and flattened with a fork.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla, salt and pecans.
Stir to coat well.
Pour on lightly buttered baking sheet or waxed paper.
Cool and separate halves.

title: almond drop cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bake at 355° for 12 minutes.

title: corned beef chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Line bottom and sides of casserole dish with corned beef and top with Mozzarella slices.
Wrap chicken pieces with bacon.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: gazpacho with sour cream
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients.
Mix with next 6 ingredients. Refrigerate. Serve with sour cream and pass with bowls of chopped celery, croutons and bacon bits.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: low-fat french toast
directions: Add egg whites, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat for 1 minute.
Coat bread by dipping in egg mixture.
Spray griddle with Pam or Wesson spray and "fry" until done.

title: burritos(quick and easy)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add meat and saute crumbling until browned.
Drain as much fat as you like. Add to meat tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, beef bouillon, seasoned salt or salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil lasagna noodles in enough water with salt and some oil 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't overcook, as they bake later.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Have ready Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer in this order:
half lasagna noodles, half meat sauce, half cottage cheese mixture, half sliced Mozzarella cheese and generously sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate, liqueur and orange juice over very low heat and set aside.
In a blender, combine whole eggs, egg yolks, vanilla and sugar and blend for 2 minutes.
Add cream and blend for another minute.
Add chocolate mixture and blend until smooth. Pour into individual serving dishes.
Top with whipped cream. Serves 4 to 6.
